{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784622868069,"sessionID":"ses_07c31cbc4ffeYIOJJ8ZhDDe6Fl","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_N9oPWUvO2mJBMRrka5mkxZhv","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"fanout_lineage_artifact_dir|FANOUT_LINEAGE_COMPLETE|phase_init|phase_main_loop","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs"},"output":"Found 8 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:\n  Line 1004:  * with config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir overriding step_resolve_artifact_root.\n\n  Line 1035:     `  config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: ${lineageDir}`,\n\n  Line 1042:     // A research lineage's phase_init binds research_topic from this line. Without it a\n\n  Line 1079:     `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir override — do NOT run the resolveArtifactRoot node`,\n\n  Line 1082:     `Run phase_init, phase_main_loop (${stopClause}), and phase_synthesis.`,\n\n  Line 1085:     `When complete, output a single line: FANOUT_LINEAGE_COMPLETE:${lineage.label}`,\n\n  Line 1123:     `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: ${lineageDir}`,\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:\n  Line 312:         'config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir',\n","metadata":{"matches":8,"truncated":false},"title":"fanout_lineage_artifact_dir|FANOUT_LINEAGE_COMPLETE|phase_init|phase_main_loop","time":{"start":1784622868036,"end":1784622868067}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09e550be9e9f04eb016a5f2f13d6f48191ad047805195f6dbb"}},"id":"prt_f83cfe6360012Pkd1Q0qvU4K4g","sessionID":"ses_07c31cbc4ffeYIOJJ8ZhDDe6Fl","messageID":"msg_f83cf9fa3001SddLMGhg9tdoGl"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784622868098,"sessionID":"ses_07c31cbc4ffeYIOJJ8ZhDDe6Fl","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_e2ZqX7CC1LVaLKGZlZS2iQCC","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml","offset":1400,"limit":700},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1400:           - graph_upsert_edges_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'edge' to edge payloads with source -> sourceId, target -> targetId, relation -> uppercase(relation), and preserve remaining edge fields\"\n1401:           - graph_upsert_event_count: \"Count mapped node and edge events\"\n1402:         if_graph_events_present:\n1403:           bash: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"research\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{graph_upsert_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_upsert_edges_json}'\"\n1404:           note: \"Skip silently when graphEvents is missing or empty.\"\n1405:         if_graph_events_missing:\n1406:           proceed: true\n1407: \n1408:       step_memory_upsert_iteration:\n1409:         action: \"Upsert the canonical iteration evidence into Spec Kit Memory after reducer and graph persistence\"\n1410:         mcp_tool: memory_save\n1411:         invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\" })'\n1412:         timeout_seconds: 5\n1413:         idempotency: \"Re-running the same iteration file is safe because the memory backend upserts by path/content.\"\n1414:         failure_policy:\n1415:           mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue\"\n1416:           timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue\"\n1417:         outputs:\n1418:           - memory_upsert_iteration_file: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1419:           - memory_upsert_status: \"upserted | advisory_error\"\n1420: \n1421:       step_refresh_memory_context:\n1422:         action: \"Refresh focused Spec Kit Memory context before the next prompt render\"\n1423:         mcp_tool: memory_context\n1424:         invocation: 'memory_context({ input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true })'\n1425:         timeout_seconds: 5\n1426:         use_response:\n1427:           - \"Update memory_context_prompt_line with a concise summary for the next step_dispatch_iteration.pre_dispatch.generate_summary.\"\n1428:         failure_policy:\n1429:           mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue with the previous memory_context_prompt_line\"\n1430:           timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue with the previous memory_context_prompt_line\"\n1431:         outputs:\n1432:           - memory_context_prompt_line: \"Fresh focused context summary for the next iteration prompt\"\n1433:           - memory_context_refresh_status: \"refreshed | advisory_error\"\n1434: \n1435:       step_evaluate_results:\n1436:         action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n1437:         verify:\n1438:           - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1439:           - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n1440:           - strategy_updated: \"Reducer refreshed strategy machine-owned sections\"\n1441:           - registry_updated: \"Reducer refreshed findings-registry.json\"\n1442:         extract:\n1443:           - newInfoRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1444:           - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1445:           - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1446:           - latest_focus: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1447:         on_missing_outputs:\n1448:           action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n1449:           # Canonical iteration record: include mode, sessionId, generation, durationMs, keyQuestions, answeredQuestions\n1450:           # so the reducer can persist the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state-format.md §Iteration Records.\n1451:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_focus}\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0,\"keyQuestions\":[],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n1452: \n1453:       step_telemetry_heartbeat_progress:\n1454:         action: \"Emit a single-loop progress row when iteration state changes\"\n1455:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n1456:         command: |\n1457:           node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1458:           import { existsSync, readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1459: \n1460:           import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n1461:           import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n1462: \n1463:           const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n1464:           const stateLogPath = '{state_paths.state_log}';\n1465:           const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n1466:           const sessionId = '{config.lineage.sessionId}';\n1467:           const generation = Number('{config.lineage.generation}');\n1468:           const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n1469: \n1470:           function readRecords(path) {\n1471:             if (!existsSync(path)) return [];\n1472:             return readFileSync(path, 'utf8')\n1473:               .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n1474:               .map((line) => line.trim())\n1475:               .filter(Boolean)\n1476:               .map((line) => JSON.parse(line));\n1477:           }\n1478: \n1479:           function elapsedSince(value) {\n1480:             const startedAtMs = Date.parse(String(value ?? ''));\n1481:             const nowMs = Date.parse(timestamp);\n1482:             if (!Number.isFinite(startedAtMs) || !Number.isFinite(nowMs)) return 0;\n1483:             return Math.max(0, nowMs - startedAtMs);\n1484:           }\n1485: \n1486:           const records = readRecords(stateLogPath);\n1487:           const iterations = records.filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration');\n1488:           const latest = iterations.at(-1) ?? {};\n1489:           const startedAt = records.find((record) => typeof record.createdAt === 'string')?.createdAt\n1490:             ?? records.find((record) => typeof record.timestamp === 'string')?.timestamp\n1491:             ?? timestamp;\n1492:           const elapsedMs = elapsedSince(startedAt);\n1493:           const score = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.newInfoRatio)) ? Number(latest.newInfoRatio) : 0;\n1494:           const run = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.run)) ? Number(latest.run) : Number('{current_iteration}');\n1495:           const status = typeof latest.status === 'string' ? latest.status : 'unknown';\n1496:           const row = {\n1497:             event: 'progress',\n1498:             label: 'single',\n1499:             at: timestamp,\n1500:             duration_ms: elapsedMs,\n1501:             loop_type: 'research',\n1502:             sessionId,\n1503:             generation,\n1504:             run,\n1505:             status,\n1506:             gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, elapsed_ms: elapsedMs, score },\n1507:           };\n1508: \n1509:           const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n1510:             diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, run, status, gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, score } },\n1511:             diffField: 'state_hash',\n1512:           });\n1513:           if (appended) {\n1514:             try {\n1515:               appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n1516:                 producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n1517:                 stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n1518:                 subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation, run },\n1519:                 event: row.event,\n1520:                 status,\n1521:               });\n1522:             } catch {}\n1523:           }\n1524:           EOF\n1525:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1526:         outputs:\n1527:           - status_ledger_progress: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event progress\"\n1528: \n1529:       step_generate_dashboard:\n1530:         action: \"Generate or refresh the human-readable dashboard\"\n1531:         read:\n1532:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1533:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1534:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1535:         template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-dashboard.md\n1536:         output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n1537:         note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + reducer registry + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n1538: \n1539:       step_update_tracking:\n1540:         action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n1541:         set:\n1542:           current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n1543:           stuck_count: \"if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip). if status == 'insight': 0 (reset). if newInfoRatio < convergence_threshold: stuck_count + 1, else: 0\"\n1544:         log: \"Iteration {N} complete. newInfoRatio: {newInfoRatio}. Findings: {findings_count}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n1545: \n1546:       step_loop_decision:\n1547:         action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n1548:         goto: step_read_state\n1549: \n1550:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1551:   # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n1552:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1553:   phase_synthesis:\n1554:     purpose: Compile all iteration findings into final research/research.md\n1555:     steps:\n1556: \n1557:       step_fanout_merge:\n1558:         description: \"Merge N lineage registries into one consolidated registry; skip when single-executor\"\n1559:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n1560:         command: |\n1561:           node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n1562:             --loop-type research \\\n1563:             --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n1564:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1565:         wait_for_completion: true\n1566: \n1567:       step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n1568:         action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n1569:         read:\n1570:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1571:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1572:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1573:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1574:         extract:\n1575:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n1576:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n1577:           - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n1578:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n1579:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n1580:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n1581:           - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n1582:           - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n1583:           - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n1584:           - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n1585:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n1586:           - divergence_summary: \"Read registry.divergence and summarize saturated directions, completed pivots, failures, overrides, Council artifact refs, and remaining frontier; else 'no divergent pivots recorded'\"\n1587:           - reason: \"Use the latest synthesis/recovery stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n1588: \n1589:       step_read_all_iterations:\n1590:         action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n1591:         read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n1592:         read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1593: \n1594:       step_emit_resource_map:\n1595:         action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged research deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n1596:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n1597:         read:\n1598:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1599:           - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n1600:         write:\n1601:           - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n1602:         guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n1603: \n1604:       step_compile_research:\n1605:         action: \"Compile or finalize research/research.md\"\n1606:         instructions: |\n1607:           If research/research.md exists (progressive synthesis was active):\n1608:             1. Read current research/research.md\n1609:             2. Consolidate and deduplicate findings across all iterations\n1610:             3. Fill any empty sections with findings from iteration files\n1611:             4. Remove redundancy while preserving all unique findings\n1612:             5. Add convergence report as appendix\n1613:             6. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n1614:             7. Preserve the mandatory `## Eliminated Alternatives` section, then add or replace `## Divergence Map` immediately after it and before Section 12 Open Questions. Populate it from `{state_paths.registry}` with saturated directions, pivots taken, evidence and Council artifact references, pivot failures and audited overrides, and the remaining frontier.\n1615: \n1616:           If research/research.md does not exist:\n1617:             1. Create research/research.md following 17-section template\n1618:             2. Populate sections from iteration files\n1619:             3. Add citations from original sources\n1620:             4. Note unanswered questions in Open Questions section\n1621:             5. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n1622:             6. After the mandatory `## Eliminated Alternatives` section and before Section 12 Open Questions, add `## Divergence Map` with saturated directions, pivots taken, evidence and Council artifact references, pivot failures and audited overrides, and the remaining frontier from `{state_paths.registry}`.\n1623:           Divergence Map documents breadth. Never claim the topic converged merely because divergent mode broadened the investigated frontier.\n1624:           Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred — see `deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract`.)\n1625:         output: \"{state_paths.research_output}\"\n1626: \n1627:       step_convergence_report:\n1628:         action: \"Generate and append convergence report\"\n1629:         report: |\n1630:           ## Convergence Report\n1631:           - Stop reason: {reason}\n1632:           - Total iterations: {iteration_count}\n1633:           - Questions answered: {answered_count} / {total_questions}\n1634:           - Remaining questions: {remaining_questions}\n1635:           - Last 3 iteration summaries: {last_3_summaries}\n1636:           - Convergence threshold: {convergence_threshold}\n1637:           - Divergence summary: {divergence_summary}\n1638:           - Segment transitions, wave scores, and checkpoint metrics are experimental and omitted from the live report.\n1639:         command: |\n1640:           node --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1641:           import { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync, statSync } from 'node:fs';\n1642: \n1643:           const paths = {\n1644:             stateLog: String.raw`{state_paths.state_log}`,\n1645:             registry: String.raw`{state_paths.registry}`,\n1646:             research: String.raw`{state_paths.research_output}`,\n1647:             dashboard: String.raw`{state_paths.dashboard}`,\n1648:           };\n1649: \n1650:           function hasFile(filePath) {\n1651:             try {\n1652:               return existsSync(filePath) && statSync(filePath).isFile();\n1653:             } catch {\n1654:               return false;\n1655:             }\n1656:           }\n1657: \n1658:           function readJson(filePath) {\n1659:             try {\n1660:               return JSON.parse(readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8'));\n1661:             } catch {\n1662:               return null;\n1663:             }\n1664:           }\n1665: \n1666:           function readJsonl(filePath) {\n1667:             if (!hasFile(filePath)) return [];\n1668:             return readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8')\n1669:               .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n1670:               .map((line) => line.trim())\n1671:               .filter(Boolean)\n1672:               .flatMap((line) => {\n1673:                 try {\n1674:                   return [JSON.parse(line)];\n1675:                 } catch {\n1676:                   return [];\n1677:                 }\n1678:               });\n1679:           }\n1680: \n1681:           function countIterationFindings(record) {\n1682:             if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration') return 0;\n1683:             const numeric = Number(record.findingsCount);\n1684:             if (Number.isFinite(numeric) && numeric > 0) return Math.floor(numeric);\n1685:             if (Array.isArray(record.keyFindings)) return record.keyFindings.length;\n1686:             if (Array.isArray(record.findings)) return record.findings.length;\n1687:             return 0;\n1688:           }\n1689: \n1690:           function normalizeFindingKey(value) {\n1691:             return String(value || '').trim().toLowerCase().replace(/\\s+/g, ' ');\n1692:           }\n1693: \n1694:           function findingKeys(candidate) {\n1695:             if (typeof candidate === 'string') {\n1696:               const key = normalizeFindingKey(candidate);\n1697:               return key ? [key] : [];\n1698:             }\n1699:             if (!candidate || typeof candidate !== 'object' || Array.isArray(candidate)) return [];\n1700:             return [...new Set([\n1701:               candidate.id,\n1702:               candidate.title,\n1703:               candidate.summary,\n1704:               candidate.text,\n1705:               candidate.finding,\n1706:               candidate.description,\n1707:             ].map(normalizeFindingKey).filter(Boolean))];\n1708:           }\n1709: \n1710:           function collectIterationFindingGroups(record) {\n1711:             if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration') return [];\n1712:             const structured = [record.keyFindings, record.findings]\n1713:               .find((value) => Array.isArray(value) && value.length > 0);\n1714:             if (!Array.isArray(structured)) return [];\n1715:             return structured\n1716:               .map(findingKeys)\n1717:               .filter((keys) => keys.length > 0);\n1718:           }\n1719: \n1720:           function collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry) {\n1721:             if (!Array.isArray(registry?.keyFindings)) return [];\n1722:             return registry.keyFindings\n1723:               .flatMap(findingKeys);\n1724:           }\n1725: \n1726:           function appendEvent(event) {\n1727:             appendFileSync(paths.stateLog, `${JSON.stringify(event)}\\n`, 'utf8');\n1728:           }\n1729: \n1730:           const registry = readJson(paths.registry);\n1731:           const registryFindingCount = Array.isArray(registry?.keyFindings) ? registry.keyFindings.length : null;\n1732:           const stateRecords = readJsonl(paths.stateLog);\n1733:           const iterationFindingCount = stateRecords.reduce((sum, record) => sum + countIterationFindings(record), 0);\n1734:           const identifiableFindingGroups = stateRecords.flatMap(collectIterationFindingGroups);\n1735:           const registryFindingKeys = new Set(collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry));\n1736:           const missingStructuredFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.filter((keys) => !keys.some((key) => registryFindingKeys.has(key))).length;\n1737:           const identifiableFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.length;\n1738:           const missingArtifacts = [\n1739:             ['registry', paths.registry],\n1740:             ['research', paths.research],\n1741:             ['dashboard', paths.dashboard],\n1742:           ].filter(([, filePath]) => !hasFile(filePath)).map(([name, filePath]) => ({ name, path: filePath }));\n1743:           const invariantFailures = [];\n1744:           if (missingArtifacts.length > 0) invariantFailures.push('missing_synthesis_artifacts');\n1745:           if (registryFindingCount === null) invariantFailures.push('registry_missing_keyFindings');\n1746:           if (iterationFindingCount > 0 && (registryFindingCount ?? 0) === 0) invariantFailures.push('state_findings_not_reflected_in_registry');\n1747:           if (identifiableFindingCount > 0 && registryFindingCount !== null && registryFindingCount < identifiableFindingCount) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_partially_reflected_in_registry');\n1748:           if (missingStructuredFindingCount > 0) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_missing_from_registry');\n1749: \n1750:           if (invariantFailures.length > 0) {\n1751:             appendEvent({\n1752:               type: 'event',\n1753:               event: 'synthesis_incomplete',\n1754:               mode: 'research',\n1755:               severity: 'warning',\n1756:               totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n1757:               answeredCount: Number('{answered_count}'),\n1758:               totalQuestions: Number('{total_questions}'),\n1759:               stopReason: '{reason}',\n1760:               reason: 'synthesis_artifact_invariant_failed',\n1761:               invariantFailures,\n1762:               missingArtifacts,\n1763:               registryFindingCount,\n1764:               iterationFindingCount,\n1765:               identifiableFindingCount,\n1766:               missingStructuredFindingCount,\n1767:               timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n1768:             });\n1769:           } else {\n1770:             appendEvent({\n1771:               type: 'event',\n1772:               event: 'synthesis_complete',\n1773:               totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n1774:               answeredCount: Number('{answered_count}'),\n1775:               totalQuestions: Number('{total_questions}'),\n1776:               stopReason: '{reason}',\n1777:               timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n1778:             });\n1779:           }\n1780:           EOF\n1781: \n1782:       step_writeback_spec_findings:\n1783:         action: \"Write or replace the bounded generated findings block in spec.md before config completion\"\n1784:         edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n1785:         host_anchor: \"Use the chosen host anchor required by spec_check_protocol\"\n1786:         generated_fence_begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\"\n1787:         generated_fence_end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\"\n1788:         fail_closed_conflict_check:\n1789:           if_existing_generated_fence_present:\n1790:             detect_manual_edits: \"Use generated checksum metadata or an explicit MANUAL-EDIT marker inside the existing fence to detect human edits before overwrite.\"\n1791:             on_manual_edit_conflict:\n1792:               append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Manual edits detected inside existing generated findings fence.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"generatedFence\":\"deep-research/spec-findings\",\"conflictKind\":\"generated-fence-manual-edit\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n1793:               halt: true\n1794:         instructions:\n1795:           - \"Read `{state_paths.research_output}` as the canonical synthesis source.\"\n1796:           - \"Replace exactly one generated findings block under the chosen host anchor.\"\n1797:           - \"Fail closed if the host anchor is missing, duplicate markers exist, or human edits are detected inside the generated block.\"\n1798:           - \"Do not overwrite a generated block that fails checksum validation or carries an explicit MANUAL-EDIT marker.\"\n1799:           - \"Emit `spec_synthesis_deferred` instead of partial output when synthesis cannot safely write back.\"\n1800:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation\",\"phase\":\"post-synthesis\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"<chosen host anchor>\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Replaced generated deep-research findings fence from research/research.md.\",\"generatedFence\":\"deep-research/spec-findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n1801: \n1802:       step_validate_post_synthesis_spec_doc:\n1803:         action: \"Run targeted strict validation after deep-research writes back into spec.md\"\n1804:         command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n1805:         note: \"Fail closed before completion if the deep-research spec.md sync breaks the authored-spec structural contract. This targeted check uses the fast Node validation orchestrator.\"\n1806: \n1807:       step_update_config_status:\n1808:         action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n1809:         edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1810:         set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n1811: \n1812:       step_telemetry_heartbeat_terminal:\n1813:         action: \"Emit a single-loop terminal row in the orchestration status ledger\"\n1814:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n1815:         terminal_events: [completed, failed, stopped]\n1816:         command: |\n1817:           node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1818:           import { existsSync, readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1819: \n1820:           import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n1821:           import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n1822: \n1823:           const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n1824:           const stateLogPath = '{state_paths.state_log}';\n1825:           const config = JSON.parse(readFileSync('{state_paths.config}', 'utf8'));\n1826:           const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n1827:           const sessionId = String(config.lineage?.sessionId ?? '{config.lineage.sessionId}');\n1828:           const generation = Number(config.lineage?.generation ?? '{config.lineage.generation}');\n1829:           const reason = '{reason}';\n1830:           const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n1831: \n1832:           function readRecords(path) {\n1833:             if (!existsSync(path)) return [];\n1834:             return readFileSync(path, 'utf8')\n1835:               .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n1836:               .map((line) => line.trim())\n1837:               .filter(Boolean)\n1838:               .map((line) => JSON.parse(line));\n1839:           }\n1840: \n1841:           function elapsedSince(value) {\n1842:             const startedAtMs = Date.parse(String(value ?? ''));\n1843:             const nowMs = Date.parse(timestamp);\n1844:             if (!Number.isFinite(startedAtMs) || !Number.isFinite(nowMs)) return 0;\n1845:             return Math.max(0, nowMs - startedAtMs);\n1846:           }\n1847: \n1848:           function terminalEvent(stopReason) {\n1849:             if (stopReason === 'manualStop' || stopReason === 'userPaused') return 'stopped';\n1850:             if (stopReason === 'error') return 'failed';\n1851:             return 'completed';\n1852:           }\n1853: \n1854:           const records = readRecords(stateLogPath);\n1855:           const iterations = records.filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration');\n1856:           const latest = iterations.at(-1) ?? {};\n1857:           const startedAt = records.find((record) => typeof record.createdAt === 'string')?.createdAt\n1858:             ?? records.find((record) => typeof record.timestamp === 'string')?.timestamp\n1859:             ?? timestamp;\n1860:           const elapsedMs = elapsedSince(startedAt);\n1861:           const score = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.newInfoRatio)) ? Number(latest.newInfoRatio) : 0;\n1862:           const event = terminalEvent(reason);\n1863:           const row = {\n1864:             event,\n1865:             label: 'single',\n1866:             terminal: true,\n1867:             reason,\n1868:             at: timestamp,\n1869:             duration_ms: elapsedMs,\n1870:             loop_type: 'research',\n1871:             sessionId,\n1872:             generation,\n1873:             gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, elapsed_ms: elapsedMs, score },\n1874:           };\n1875: \n1876:           const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n1877:             diffData: { event, label: row.label, reason, sessionId, generation, gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, score } },\n1878:             diffField: 'state_hash',\n1879:           });\n1880:           if (appended) {\n1881:             try {\n1882:               appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n1883:                 producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n1884:                 stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n1885:                 subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation, reason },\n1886:                 event,\n1887:                 status: event,\n1888:               });\n1889:             } catch {}\n1890:           }\n1891:           EOF\n1892:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1893:         outputs:\n1894:           - status_ledger_terminal: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event completed, failed, or stopped\"\n1895: \n1896:       step_stage_artifact_dir:\n1897:         action: \"Stage all skill-owned artifacts under artifact_dir for the operator's next git commit\"\n1898:         command: \"git add {state_paths.packet_dir}\"\n1899:         note: \"Skill-owned contract fix (028): without this stage step, operators who do `git add research-report.md` lose the iteration trail (iterations/, deltas/, state.jsonl, strategy, etc.). Staging the whole artifact_dir keeps the audit trail intact. Operators retain commit authority and can `git restore --staged {path}` to unstage anything before commit. Failure is non-fatal — log warning and continue.\"\n1900:         on_fail: \"Log warning. Do not block synthesis. The artifact_dir may be outside a git repo (e.g., temp test fixture) which is a valid case.\"\n1901: \n1902:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1903:   # PHASE 4: SAVE\n1904:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1905:   phase_save:\n1906:     purpose: Preserve research context to memory system\n1907:     steps:\n1908: \n1909:       step_compose_save_payload:\n1910:         action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n1911:         output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n1912:         requirements:\n1913:           - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n1914:           - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed research loop.\"\n1915:           - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n1916:         example_payload: |\n1917:           {\n1918:             \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n1919:             \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep research completed; see research/research.md for synthesized findings.\",\n1920:             \"observations\": [\"Summarize the final research conclusions and evidence.\"],\n1921:             \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated research artifacts and next action.\"],\n1922:             \"exchanges\": [],\n1923:             \"toolCalls\": []\n1924:           }\n1925: \n1926:       step_generate_context:\n1927:         action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n1928:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n1929:         critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n1930: \n1931:       step_index_memory:\n1932:         action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n1933:         mcp_tool: memory_save\n1934:         invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n1935:         note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n1936: \n1937:       step_verify_save:\n1938:         action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n1939:         check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n1940:         on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n1941: \n1942:       step_release_lock:\n1943:         action: \"Release the single-writer lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n1944:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n1945:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n1946: \n1947:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1948:   # COMPLETION\n1949:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1950:   completion:\n1951:     message: |\n1952:       Deep research complete.\n1953:       Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n1954:       Questions answered: {answered_count}/{total_questions}\n1955: \n1956:       Artifacts:\n1957:         - research/research.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n1958:         - {iteration_count} iteration files in research/\n1959:         - State files: config.json, state.jsonl, strategy.md, findings-registry.json, dashboard.md\n1960:         - Memory context saved\n1961: \n1962:       STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n1963:     next_steps:\n1964:       - \"/speckit:plan [feature-description]\"\n1965:       - \"/deep:research [new-topic] (for related deep research)\"\n1966:       - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n1967: \n1968: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1969: # ERROR RECOVERY\n1970: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1971: error_recovery:\n1972:   agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer research actions). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n1973:   state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n1974:   consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n1975:   memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the research/ packet as backup. Log warning.\"\n1976: \n1977: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1978: # RULES\n1979: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1980: rules:\n1981:   ALWAYS:\n1982:     - follow_workflow_phases_in_order\n1983:     - dispatch_deep_research_agent_per_iteration\n1984:     - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n1985:     - write_all_state_to_files\n1986:     - upsert_iteration_memory_after_reducer\n1987:     - refresh_memory_context_before_next_prompt\n1988:     - save_memory_context_after_synthesis\n1989:     - respect_max_iterations_cap\n1990:   NEVER:\n1991:     - skip_convergence_check\n1992:     - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n1993:     - hold_iteration_findings_in_memory_only\n1994:     - modify_config_after_initialization\n1995:     - overwrite_jsonl_state_log\n1996:     - proceed_without_state_file_verification\n1997: \n1998: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1999: # REFERENCE-ONLY APPENDIX\n2000: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2001: reference_only_appendix:\n2002:   checkpoint_commit:\n2003:     note: \"Checkpoint commits are intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n2004:     commands:\n2005:       - \"git add {state_paths.iteration_pattern} {state_paths.state_log} {state_paths.strategy} {state_paths.research_output}\"\n2006:       - 'git commit -m \"chore(deep-research): iteration {NNN} complete\"'\n2007:   wave_orchestration:\n2008:     note: \"Wave execution is intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n2009:     summary:\n2010:       - \"Check whether 3+ independent unanswered questions justify a wave.\"\n2011:       - \"Dispatch up to 3 parallel agents on distinct questions.\"\n2012:       - \"Score wave results by median newInfoRatio and promote top branches.\"\n\n(End of file - total 2012 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"          - graph_upsert_edges_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'edge' to edge payloads with source -> sourceId, target -> targetId, relation -> uppercase(relation), and preserve remaining edge fields\"\n          - graph_upsert_event_count: \"Count mapped node and edge events\"\n        if_graph_events_present:\n          bash: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"research\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{graph_upsert_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_upsert_edges_json}'\"\n          note: \"Skip silently when graphEvents is missing or empty.\"\n        if_graph_events_missing:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_memory_upsert_iteration:\n        action: \"Upsert the canonical iteration evidence into Spec Kit Memory after reducer and graph persistence\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_save\n        invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\" })'\n        timeout_seconds: 5\n        idempotency: \"Re-running the same iteration file is safe because the memory backend upserts by path/content.\"\n        failure_policy:\n          mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue\"\n          timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue\"\n        outputs:\n          - memory_upsert_iteration_file: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - memory_upsert_status: \"upserted | advisory_error\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml","text":"          - graph_upsert_edges_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'edge' to edge payloads with source -> sourceId, target -> targetId, relation -> uppercase(relation), and preserve remaining edge fields\"\n          - graph_upsert_event_count: \"Count mapped node and edge events\"\n        if_graph_events_present:\n          bash: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"research\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{graph_upsert_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_upsert_edges_json}'\"\n          note: \"Skip silently when graphEvents is missing or empty.\"\n        if_graph_events_missing:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_memory_upsert_iteration:\n        action: \"Upsert the canonical iteration evidence into Spec Kit Memory after reducer and graph persistence\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_save\n        invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\" })'\n        timeout_seconds: 5\n        idempotency: \"Re-running the same iteration file is safe because the memory backend upserts by path/content.\"\n        failure_policy:\n          mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue\"\n          timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue\"\n        outputs:\n          - memory_upsert_iteration_file: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - memory_upsert_status: \"upserted | advisory_error\"\n\n      step_refresh_memory_context:\n        action: \"Refresh focused Spec Kit Memory context before the next prompt render\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_context\n        invocation: 'memory_context({ input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true })'\n        timeout_seconds: 5\n        use_response:\n          - \"Update memory_context_prompt_line with a concise summary for the next step_dispatch_iteration.pre_dispatch.generate_summary.\"\n        failure_policy:\n          mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue with the previous memory_context_prompt_line\"\n          timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue with the previous memory_context_prompt_line\"\n        outputs:\n          - memory_context_prompt_line: \"Fresh focused context summary for the next iteration prompt\"\n          - memory_context_refresh_status: \"refreshed | advisory_error\"\n\n      step_evaluate_results:\n        action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n        verify:\n          - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n          - strategy_updated: \"Reducer refreshed strategy machine-owned sections\"\n          - registry_updated: \"Reducer refreshed findings-registry.json\"\n        extract:\n          - newInfoRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - latest_focus: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n        on_missing_outputs:\n          action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n          # Canonical iteration record: include mode, sessionId, generation, durationMs, keyQuestions, answeredQuestions\n          # so the reducer can persist the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state-format.md §Iteration Records.\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_focus}\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0,\"keyQuestions\":[],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_telemetry_heartbeat_progress:\n        action: \"Emit a single-loop progress row when iteration state changes\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n        command: |\n          node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { existsSync, readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n          import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n\n          const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n          const stateLogPath = '{state_paths.state_log}';\n          const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n          const sessionId = '{config.lineage.sessionId}';\n          const generation = Number('{config.lineage.generation}');\n          const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n\n          function readRecords(path) {\n            if (!existsSync(path)) return [];\n            return readFileSync(path, 'utf8')\n              .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n              .map((line) => line.trim())\n              .filter(Boolean)\n              .map((line) => JSON.parse(line));\n          }\n\n          function elapsedSince(value) {\n            const startedAtMs = Date.parse(String(value ?? ''));\n            const nowMs = Date.parse(timestamp);\n            if (!Number.isFinite(startedAtMs) || !Number.isFinite(nowMs)) return 0;\n            return Math.max(0, nowMs - startedAtMs);\n          }\n\n          const records = readRecords(stateLogPath);\n          const iterations = records.filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration');\n          const latest = iterations.at(-1) ?? {};\n          const startedAt = records.find((record) => typeof record.createdAt === 'string')?.createdAt\n            ?? records.find((record) => typeof record.timestamp === 'string')?.timestamp\n            ?? timestamp;\n          const elapsedMs = elapsedSince(startedAt);\n          const score = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.newInfoRatio)) ? Number(latest.newInfoRatio) : 0;\n          const run = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.run)) ? Number(latest.run) : Number('{current_iteration}');\n          const status = typeof latest.status === 'string' ? latest.status : 'unknown';\n          const row = {\n            event: 'progress',\n            label: 'single',\n            at: timestamp,\n            duration_ms: elapsedMs,\n            loop_type: 'research',\n            sessionId,\n            generation,\n            run,\n            status,\n            gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, elapsed_ms: elapsedMs, score },\n          };\n\n          const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n            diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, run, status, gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, score } },\n            diffField: 'state_hash',\n          });\n          if (appended) {\n            try {\n              appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n                producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n                stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n                subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation, run },\n                event: row.event,\n                status,\n              });\n            } catch {}\n          }\n          EOF\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        outputs:\n          - status_ledger_progress: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event progress\"\n\n      step_generate_dashboard:\n        action: \"Generate or refresh the human-readable dashboard\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-dashboard.md\n        output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n        note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + reducer registry + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n\n      step_update_tracking:\n        action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n        set:\n          current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n          stuck_count: \"if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip). if status == 'insight': 0 (reset). if newInfoRatio < convergence_threshold: stuck_count + 1, else: 0\"\n        log: \"Iteration {N} complete. newInfoRatio: {newInfoRatio}. Findings: {findings_count}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n\n      step_loop_decision:\n        action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n        goto: step_read_state\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_synthesis:\n    purpose: Compile all iteration findings into final research/research.md\n    steps:\n\n      step_fanout_merge:\n        description: \"Merge N lineage registries into one consolidated registry; skip when single-executor\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n            --loop-type research \\\n            --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n      step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n        action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n          - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n          - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n          - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n          - divergence_summary: \"Read registry.divergence and summarize saturated directions, completed pivots, failures, overrides, Council artifact refs, and remaining frontier; else 'no divergent pivots recorded'\"\n          - reason: \"Use the latest synthesis/recovery stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n\n      step_read_all_iterations:\n        action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n        read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n        read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_emit_resource_map:\n        action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged research deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n        guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n\n      step_compile_research:\n        action: \"Compile or finalize research/research.md\"\n        instructions: |\n          If research/research.md exists (progressive synthesis was active):\n            1. Read current research/research.md\n            2. Consolidate and deduplicate findings across all iterations\n            3. Fill any empty sections with findings from iteration files\n            4. Remove redundancy while preserving all unique findings\n            5. Add convergence report as appendix\n            6. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n            7. Preserve the mandatory `## Eliminated Alternatives` section, then add or replace `## Divergence Map` immediately after it and before Section 12 Open Questions. Populate it from `{state_paths.registry}` with saturated directions, pivots taken, evidence and Council artifact references, pivot failures and audited overrides, and the remaining frontier.\n\n          If research/research.md does not exist:\n            1. Create research/research.md following 17-section template\n            2. Populate sections from iteration files\n            3. Add citations from original sources\n            4. Note unanswered questions in Open Questions section\n            5. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n            6. After the mandatory `## Eliminated Alternatives` section and before Section 12 Open Questions, add `## Divergence Map` with saturated directions, pivots taken, evidence and Council artifact references, pivot failures and audited overrides, and the remaining frontier from `{state_paths.registry}`.\n          Divergence Map documents breadth. Never claim the topic converged merely because divergent mode broadened the investigated frontier.\n          Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred — see `deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract`.)\n        output: \"{state_paths.research_output}\"\n\n      step_convergence_report:\n        action: \"Generate and append convergence report\"\n        report: |\n          ## Convergence Report\n          - Stop reason: {reason}\n          - Total iterations: {iteration_count}\n          - Questions answered: {answered_count} / {total_questions}\n          - Remaining questions: {remaining_questions}\n          - Last 3 iteration summaries: {last_3_summaries}\n          - Convergence threshold: {convergence_threshold}\n          - Divergence summary: {divergence_summary}\n          - Segment transitions, wave scores, and checkpoint metrics are experimental and omitted from the live report.\n        command: |\n          node --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync, statSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          const paths = {\n            stateLog: String.raw`{state_paths.state_log}`,\n            registry: String.raw`{state_paths.registry}`,\n            research: String.raw`{state_paths.research_output}`,\n            dashboard: String.raw`{state_paths.dashboard}`,\n          };\n\n          function hasFile(filePath) {\n            try {\n              return existsSync(filePath) && statSync(filePath).isFile();\n            } catch {\n              return false;\n            }\n          }\n\n          function readJson(filePath) {\n            try {\n              return JSON.parse(readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8'));\n            } catch {\n              return null;\n            }\n          }\n\n          function readJsonl(filePath) {\n            if (!hasFile(filePath)) return [];\n            return readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8')\n              .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n              .map((line) => line.trim())\n              .filter(Boolean)\n              .flatMap((line) => {\n                try {\n                  return [JSON.parse(line)];\n                } catch {\n                  return [];\n                }\n              });\n          }\n\n          function countIterationFindings(record) {\n            if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration') return 0;\n            const numeric = Number(record.findingsCount);\n            if (Number.isFinite(numeric) && numeric > 0) return Math.floor(numeric);\n            if (Array.isArray(record.keyFindings)) return record.keyFindings.length;\n            if (Array.isArray(record.findings)) return record.findings.length;\n            return 0;\n          }\n\n          function normalizeFindingKey(value) {\n            return String(value || '').trim().toLowerCase().replace(/\\s+/g, ' ');\n          }\n\n          function findingKeys(candidate) {\n            if (typeof candidate === 'string') {\n              const key = normalizeFindingKey(candidate);\n              return key ? [key] : [];\n            }\n            if (!candidate || typeof candidate !== 'object' || Array.isArray(candidate)) return [];\n            return [...new Set([\n              candidate.id,\n              candidate.title,\n              candidate.summary,\n              candidate.text,\n              candidate.finding,\n              candidate.description,\n            ].map(normalizeFindingKey).filter(Boolean))];\n          }\n\n          function collectIterationFindingGroups(record) {\n            if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration') return [];\n            const structured = [record.keyFindings, record.findings]\n              .find((value) => Array.isArray(value) && value.length > 0);\n            if (!Array.isArray(structured)) return [];\n            return structured\n              .map(findingKeys)\n              .filter((keys) => keys.length > 0);\n          }\n\n          function collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry) {\n            if (!Array.isArray(registry?.keyFindings)) return [];\n            return registry.keyFindings\n              .flatMap(findingKeys);\n          }\n\n          function appendEvent(event) {\n            appendFileSync(paths.stateLog, `${JSON.stringify(event)}\\n`, 'utf8');\n          }\n\n          const registry = readJson(paths.registry);\n          const registryFindingCount = Array.isArray(registry?.keyFindings) ? registry.keyFindings.length : null;\n          const stateRecords = readJsonl(paths.stateLog);\n          const iterationFindingCount = stateRecords.reduce((sum, record) => sum + countIterationFindings(record), 0);\n          const identifiableFindingGroups = stateRecords.flatMap(collectIterationFindingGroups);\n          const registryFindingKeys = new Set(collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry));\n          const missingStructuredFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.filter((keys) => !keys.some((key) => registryFindingKeys.has(key))).length;\n          const identifiableFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.length;\n          const missingArtifacts = [\n            ['registry', paths.registry],\n            ['research', paths.research],\n            ['dashboard', paths.dashboard],\n          ].filter(([, filePath]) => !hasFile(filePath)).map(([name, filePath]) => ({ name, path: filePath }));\n          const invariantFailures = [];\n          if (missingArtifacts.length > 0) invariantFailures.push('missing_synthesis_artifacts');\n          if (registryFindingCount === null) invariantFailures.push('registry_missing_keyFindings');\n          if (iterationFindingCount > 0 && (registryFindingCount ?? 0) === 0) invariantFailures.push('state_findings_not_reflected_in_registry');\n          if (identifiableFindingCount > 0 && registryFindingCount !== null && registryFindingCount < identifiableFindingCount) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_partially_reflected_in_registry');\n          if (missingStructuredFindingCount > 0) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_missing_from_registry');\n\n          if (invariantFailures.length > 0) {\n            appendEvent({\n              type: 'event',\n              event: 'synthesis_incomplete',\n              mode: 'research',\n              severity: 'warning',\n              totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n              answeredCount: Number('{answered_count}'),\n              totalQuestions: Number('{total_questions}'),\n              stopReason: '{reason}',\n              reason: 'synthesis_artifact_invariant_failed',\n              invariantFailures,\n              missingArtifacts,\n              registryFindingCount,\n              iterationFindingCount,\n              identifiableFindingCount,\n              missingStructuredFindingCount,\n              timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n            });\n          } else {\n            appendEvent({\n              type: 'event',\n              event: 'synthesis_complete',\n              totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n              answeredCount: Number('{answered_count}'),\n              totalQuestions: Number('{total_questions}'),\n              stopReason: '{reason}',\n              timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n            });\n          }\n          EOF\n\n      step_writeback_spec_findings:\n        action: \"Write or replace the bounded generated findings block in spec.md before config completion\"\n        edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n        host_anchor: \"Use the chosen host anchor required by spec_check_protocol\"\n        generated_fence_begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\"\n        generated_fence_end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\"\n        fail_closed_conflict_check:\n          if_existing_generated_fence_present:\n            detect_manual_edits: \"Use generated checksum metadata or an explicit MANUAL-EDIT marker inside the existing fence to detect human edits before overwrite.\"\n            on_manual_edit_conflict:\n              append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Manual edits detected inside existing generated findings fence.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"generatedFence\":\"deep-research/spec-findings\",\"conflictKind\":\"generated-fence-manual-edit\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n              halt: true\n        instructions:\n          - \"Read `{state_paths.research_output}` as the canonical synthesis source.\"\n          - \"Replace exactly one generated findings block under the chosen host anchor.\"\n          - \"Fail closed if the host anchor is missing, duplicate markers exist, or human edits are detected inside the generated block.\"\n          - \"Do not overwrite a generated block that fails checksum validation or carries an explicit MANUAL-EDIT marker.\"\n          - \"Emit `spec_synthesis_deferred` instead of partial output when synthesis cannot safely write back.\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation\",\"phase\":\"post-synthesis\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"<chosen host anchor>\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Replaced generated deep-research findings fence from research/research.md.\",\"generatedFence\":\"deep-research/spec-findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_validate_post_synthesis_spec_doc:\n        action: \"Run targeted strict validation after deep-research writes back into spec.md\"\n        command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n        note: \"Fail closed before completion if the deep-research spec.md sync breaks the authored-spec structural contract. This targeted check uses the fast Node validation orchestrator.\"\n\n      step_update_config_status:\n        action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n\n      step_telemetry_heartbeat_terminal:\n        action: \"Emit a single-loop terminal row in the orchestration status ledger\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n        terminal_events: [completed, failed, stopped]\n        command: |\n          node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { existsSync, readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n          import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n\n          const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n          const stateLogPath = '{state_paths.state_log}';\n          const config = JSON.parse(readFileSync('{state_paths.config}', 'utf8'));\n          const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n          const sessionId = String(config.lineage?.sessionId ?? '{config.lineage.sessionId}');\n          const generation = Number(config.lineage?.generation ?? '{config.lineage.generation}');\n          const reason = '{reason}';\n          const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n\n          function readRecords(path) {\n            if (!existsSync(path)) return [];\n            return readFileSync(path, 'utf8')\n              .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n              .map((line) => line.trim())\n              .filter(Boolean)\n              .map((line) => JSON.parse(line));\n          }\n\n          function elapsedSince(value) {\n            const startedAtMs = Date.parse(String(value ?? ''));\n            const nowMs = Date.parse(timestamp);\n            if (!Number.isFinite(startedAtMs) || !Number.isFinite(nowMs)) return 0;\n            return Math.max(0, nowMs - startedAtMs);\n          }\n\n          function terminalEvent(stopReason) {\n            if (stopReason === 'manualStop' || stopReason === 'userPaused') return 'stopped';\n            if (stopReason === 'error') return 'failed';\n            return 'completed';\n          }\n\n          const records = readRecords(stateLogPath);\n          const iterations = records.filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration');\n          const latest = iterations.at(-1) ?? {};\n          const startedAt = records.find((record) => typeof record.createdAt === 'string')?.createdAt\n            ?? records.find((record) => typeof record.timestamp === 'string')?.timestamp\n            ?? timestamp;\n          const elapsedMs = elapsedSince(startedAt);\n          const score = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.newInfoRatio)) ? Number(latest.newInfoRatio) : 0;\n          const event = terminalEvent(reason);\n          const row = {\n            event,\n            label: 'single',\n            terminal: true,\n            reason,\n            at: timestamp,\n            duration_ms: elapsedMs,\n            loop_type: 'research',\n            sessionId,\n            generation,\n            gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, elapsed_ms: elapsedMs, score },\n          };\n\n          const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n            diffData: { event, label: row.label, reason, sessionId, generation, gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, score } },\n            diffField: 'state_hash',\n          });\n          if (appended) {\n            try {\n              appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n                producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n                stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n                subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation, reason },\n                event,\n                status: event,\n              });\n            } catch {}\n          }\n          EOF\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        outputs:\n          - status_ledger_terminal: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event completed, failed, or stopped\"\n\n      step_stage_artifact_dir:\n        action: \"Stage all skill-owned artifacts under artifact_dir for the operator's next git commit\"\n        command: \"git add {state_paths.packet_dir}\"\n        note: \"Skill-owned contract fix (028): without this stage step, operators who do `git add research-report.md` lose the iteration trail (iterations/, deltas/, state.jsonl, strategy, etc.). Staging the whole artifact_dir keeps the audit trail intact. Operators retain commit authority and can `git restore --staged {path}` to unstage anything before commit. Failure is non-fatal — log warning and continue.\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning. Do not block synthesis. The artifact_dir may be outside a git repo (e.g., temp test fixture) which is a valid case.\"\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 4: SAVE\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_save:\n    purpose: Preserve research context to memory system\n    steps:\n\n      step_compose_save_payload:\n        action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n        output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n        requirements:\n          - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n          - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed research loop.\"\n          - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n        example_payload: |\n          {\n            \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n            \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep research completed; see research/research.md for synthesized findings.\",\n            \"observations\": [\"Summarize the final research conclusions and evidence.\"],\n            \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated research artifacts and next action.\"],\n            \"exchanges\": [],\n            \"toolCalls\": []\n          }\n\n      step_generate_context:\n        action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n        critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n\n      step_index_memory:\n        action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_save\n        invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n        note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n\n      step_verify_save:\n        action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n        check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n\n      step_release_lock:\n        action: \"Release the single-writer lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # COMPLETION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  completion:\n    message: |\n      Deep research complete.\n      Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n      Questions answered: {answered_count}/{total_questions}\n\n      Artifacts:\n        - research/research.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n        - {iteration_count} iteration files in research/\n        - State files: config.json, state.jsonl, strategy.md, findings-registry.json, dashboard.md\n        - Memory context saved\n\n      STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n    next_steps:\n      - \"/speckit:plan [feature-description]\"\n      - \"/deep:research [new-topic] (for related deep research)\"\n      - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# ERROR RECOVERY\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nerror_recovery:\n  agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer research actions). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n  state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n  consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n  memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the research/ packet as backup. Log warning.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# RULES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrules:\n  ALWAYS:\n    - follow_workflow_phases_in_order\n    - dispatch_deep_research_agent_per_iteration\n    - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n    - write_all_state_to_files\n    - upsert_iteration_memory_after_reducer\n    - refresh_memory_context_before_next_prompt\n    - save_memory_context_after_synthesis\n    - respect_max_iterations_cap\n  NEVER:\n    - skip_convergence_check\n    - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n    - hold_iteration_findings_in_memory_only\n    - modify_config_after_initialization\n    - overwrite_jsonl_state_log\n    - proceed_without_state_file_verification\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# REFERENCE-ONLY APPENDIX\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nreference_only_appendix:\n  checkpoint_commit:\n    note: \"Checkpoint commits are intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n    commands:\n      - \"git add {state_paths.iteration_pattern} {state_paths.state_log} {state_paths.strategy} {state_paths.research_output}\"\n      - 'git commit -m \"chore(deep-research): iteration {NNN} complete\"'\n  wave_orchestration:\n    note: \"Wave execution is intentionally excluded from workflow.steps.\"\n    summary:\n      - \"Check whether 3+ independent unanswered questions justify a wave.\"\n      - \"Dispatch up to 3 parallel agents on distinct questions.\"\n      - \"Score wave results by median newInfoRatio and promote top branches.\"","lineStart":1400,"lineEnd":2012,"totalLines":2012,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml","time":{"start":1784622868017,"end":1784622868084}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09e550be9e9f04eb016a5f2f13d6c481918acdd77fd07e1f2e"}},"id":"prt_f83cfe5db001oItEzyH7t0ZxRk","sessionID":"ses_07c31cbc4ffeYIOJJ8ZhDDe6Fl","messageID":"msg_f83cf9fa3001SddLMGhg9tdoGl"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784622868098,"sessionID":"ses_07c31cbc4ffeYIOJJ8ZhDDe6Fl","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_4DSaiJga6aU3zxbD8VeP9xB5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/feature-catalog/fanout/fanout-run.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/feature-catalog/fanout/fanout-run.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Fan-out CLI lineage driver\"\n3: description: \"CLI lineage pool driver: TSX-bootstrapped entry point that spawns N headless CLI subprocesses (opencode, claude, opencode), each running the full loop in an isolated lineages/{label}/ sub-packet, with per-kind state-dir isolation and a post-subprocess salvage sweep.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"fan-out cli lineage driver\"\n6:   - \"fanout-run.cjs\"\n7:   - \"spawn fanout lineages\"\n8:   - \"per-kind state-dir isolation\"\n9:   - \"cli subprocess fanout dispatch\"\n10: version: 1.4.0.4\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Fan-out CLI lineage driver\n14: \n15: <!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n20: \n21: `fanout-run.cjs` bridges the pool primitive and the actual CLI executor subprocesses. It\n22: parses the fanout config JSON, filters to CLI lineages (native lineages are handled by the\n23: YAML `step_fanout_spawn_native` agent dispatch), creates `{base}/lineages/{label}/` and\n24: `{label}/.executor-state/` directories per lineage, builds a \"run the full loop\" prompt,\n25: constructs the per-kind CLI command (`opencode run` + stdin, `claude -p`, `opencode run` +\n26: `</dev/null`), sets\n27: `SPECKIT_FANOUT_LINEAGE_ID={label}` and `SPECKIT_<KIND>_STATE_DIR={stateDir}` environment\n28: variables to prevent same-kind replica lockfile collisions, runs via `spawnSync` with a\n29: generous timeout, saves subprocess stdout to `{lineageDir}/logs/fanout-lineage.out`, then\n30: calls `runSalvageSweep` from `fanout-salvage.cjs`.\n31: \n32: ### Why This Matters\n33: \n34: Dispatches every CLI executor fan-out lineage. If this drifts, parallel research/review\n35: runs can produce mis-isolated sub-packets, lose the per-kind state-dir isolation, or miss\n36: the post-subprocess salvage step.\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ## 2. HOW IT WORKS\n41: \n42: Fully shipped. Supports all 3 CLI kinds: `cli-opencode`, `cli-claude-code`, `cli-opencode`.\n43: Per-lineage subprocess timeout = `min(iterations *\n44: timeoutSeconds * 2, 4h)`. TSX bootstrap (mirrors `convergence.cjs` pattern) ensures\n45: TypeScript imports (`parseFanoutConfig`, `expandLineages`) resolve in the CJS context. Exit\n46: codes: 0=all ok, 2=some failed, 3=all failed.\n47: \n48: The driver also carries an optional per-lineage progress-heartbeat gauge.\n49: `startLineageProgressHeartbeat` emits periodic progress events at the configured cadence so a\n50: long-running lineage stays operator-readable. The cadence comes from the\n51: `progressHeartbeatSeconds` config field, whose committed default is 0 (disabled), so the\n52: gauge is opt-in. The recommended production cadence is 30 seconds.\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ## 3. SOURCE FILES\n57: \n58: ### Implementation\n59: \n60: | File | Role |\n61: |---|---|\n62: | `scripts/fanout-run.cjs` | Main entry: CLI arg parsing, per-kind command construction, pool orchestration, stdout capture and salvage call, plus the per-lineage progress heartbeat via `startLineageProgressHeartbeat` |\n63: | `scripts/fanout-salvage.cjs` | Called post-subprocess for write-failure recovery |\n64: | `scripts/fanout-pool.cjs` | `runCappedPool` for concurrency cap + ledger |\n65: | `lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts` | `parseFanoutConfig`, `expandLineages` imported via TSX |\n66: | `lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts` | `EXECUTOR_STATE_ENV_BY_KIND` constants for per-kind state dir naming |\n67: \n68: ### Validation\n69: \n70: | File | Role |\n71: |---|---|\n72: | `tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts` | 5 tests: native-only config returns early (no pool spawn), bad JSON config exits 3, missing required args exits 3, 2-lineage pool creates distinct dirs + ledger + summary, same-kind replica state dirs are distinct |\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## 4. SOURCE METADATA\n77: \n78: - Group: Fan-Out\n79: - Feature ID: F025\n80: - Catalog source: `feature-catalog/fanout/fanout-run.md`\n81: - Primary source files: `scripts/fanout-run.cjs`\n82: Related references:\n83: - [fanout-pool.md](../../feature-catalog/fanout/fanout-pool.md) — Fan-out worker pool\n84: - [fanout-salvage.md](../../feature-catalog/fanout/fanout-salvage.md) — Fan-out write-failure salvage\n\n(End of file - total 84 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Fan-out CLI lineage driver\"\ndescription: \"CLI lineage pool driver: TSX-bootstrapped entry point that spawns N headless CLI subprocesses (opencode, claude, opencode), each running the full loop in an isolated lineages/{label}/ sub-packet, with per-kind state-dir isolation and a post-subprocess salvage sweep.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"fan-out cli lineage driver\"\n  - \"fanout-run.cjs\"\n  - \"spawn fanout lineages\"\n  - \"per-kind state-dir isolation\"\n  - \"cli subprocess fanout dispatch\"\nversion: 1.4.0.4\n---\n\n# Fan-out CLI lineage driver\n\n<!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/feature-catalog/fanout/fanout-run.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Fan-out CLI lineage driver\"\ndescription: \"CLI lineage pool driver: TSX-bootstrapped entry point that spawns N headless CLI subprocesses (opencode, claude, opencode), each running the full loop in an isolated lineages/{label}/ sub-packet, with per-kind state-dir isolation and a post-subprocess salvage sweep.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"fan-out cli lineage driver\"\n  - \"fanout-run.cjs\"\n  - \"spawn fanout lineages\"\n  - \"per-kind state-dir isolation\"\n  - \"cli subprocess fanout dispatch\"\nversion: 1.4.0.4\n---\n\n# Fan-out CLI lineage driver\n\n<!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n`fanout-run.cjs` bridges the pool primitive and the actual CLI executor subprocesses. It\nparses the fanout config JSON, filters to CLI lineages (native lineages are handled by the\nYAML `step_fanout_spawn_native` agent dispatch), creates `{base}/lineages/{label}/` and\n`{label}/.executor-state/` directories per lineage, builds a \"run the full loop\" prompt,\nconstructs the per-kind CLI command (`opencode run` + stdin, `claude -p`, `opencode run` +\n`</dev/null`), sets\n`SPECKIT_FANOUT_LINEAGE_ID={label}` and `SPECKIT_<KIND>_STATE_DIR={stateDir}` environment\nvariables to prevent same-kind replica lockfile collisions, runs via `spawnSync` with a\ngenerous timeout, saves subprocess stdout to `{lineageDir}/logs/fanout-lineage.out`, then\ncalls `runSalvageSweep` from `fanout-salvage.cjs`.\n\n### Why This Matters\n\nDispatches every CLI executor fan-out lineage. If this drifts, parallel research/review\nruns can produce mis-isolated sub-packets, lose the per-kind state-dir isolation, or miss\nthe post-subprocess salvage step.\n\n---\n\n## 2. HOW IT WORKS\n\nFully shipped. Supports all 3 CLI kinds: `cli-opencode`, `cli-claude-code`, `cli-opencode`.\nPer-lineage subprocess timeout = `min(iterations *\ntimeoutSeconds * 2, 4h)`. TSX bootstrap (mirrors `convergence.cjs` pattern) ensures\nTypeScript imports (`parseFanoutConfig`, `expandLineages`) resolve in the CJS context. Exit\ncodes: 0=all ok, 2=some failed, 3=all failed.\n\nThe driver also carries an optional per-lineage progress-heartbeat gauge.\n`startLineageProgressHeartbeat` emits periodic progress events at the configured cadence so a\nlong-running lineage stays operator-readable. The cadence comes from the\n`progressHeartbeatSeconds` config field, whose committed default is 0 (disabled), so the\ngauge is opt-in. The recommended production cadence is 30 seconds.\n\n---\n\n## 3. SOURCE FILES\n\n### Implementation\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `scripts/fanout-run.cjs` | Main entry: CLI arg parsing, per-kind command construction, pool orchestration, stdout capture and salvage call, plus the per-lineage progress heartbeat via `startLineageProgressHeartbeat` |\n| `scripts/fanout-salvage.cjs` | Called post-subprocess for write-failure recovery |\n| `scripts/fanout-pool.cjs` | `runCappedPool` for concurrency cap + ledger |\n| `lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts` | `parseFanoutConfig`, `expandLineages` imported via TSX |\n| `lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts` | `EXECUTOR_STATE_ENV_BY_KIND` constants for per-kind state dir naming |\n\n### Validation\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts` | 5 tests: native-only config returns early (no pool spawn), bad JSON config exits 3, missing required args exits 3, 2-lineage pool creates distinct dirs + ledger + summary, same-kind replica state dirs are distinct |\n\n---\n\n## 4. SOURCE METADATA\n\n- Group: Fan-Out\n- Feature ID: F025\n- Catalog source: `feature-catalog/fanout/fanout-run.md`\n- Primary source files: `scripts/fanout-run.cjs`\nRelated references:\n- [fanout-pool.md](../../feature-catalog/fanout/fanout-pool.md) — Fan-out worker pool\n- [fanout-salvage.md](../../feature-catalog/fanout/fanout-salvage.md) — Fan-out write-failure salvage","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":84,"totalLines":84,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/feature-catalog/fanout/fanout-run.md","time":{"start":1784622868041,"end":1784622868088}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09e550be9e9f04eb016a5f2f13d7088191b9604fff7fcb25dd"}},"id":"prt_f83cfe646001kfgxPs34jx1vP7","sessionID":"ses_07c31cbc4ffeYIOJJ8ZhDDe6Fl","messageID":"msg_f83cf9fa3001SddLMGhg9tdoGl"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784622868098,"sessionID":"ses_07c31cbc4ffeYIOJJ8ZhDDe6Fl","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_yxXhAzeFgzwGIsaZ9ddQKOgL","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/manual-testing-playbook/fanout/fanout-run-cli-lineage-spawn.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/manual-testing-playbook/fanout/fanout-run-cli-lineage-spawn.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"DLR-025 -- Fan-out CLI lineage driver spawn and isolation\"\n3: description: \"Validate fanout-run.cjs creates per-lineage dirs with isolated .executor-state paths, saves stdout to logs/, writes orchestration summary and ledger, and returns early for native-only configs.\"\n4: version: 1.4.0.4\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # DLR-025 -- Fan-out CLI lineage driver spawn and isolation\n8: \n9: This document captures the validation contract, execution flow, and metadata for `DLR-025`.\n10: \n11: ---\n12: \n13: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n14: \n15: Validates the CLI lineage pool driver `fanout-run.cjs` — specifically lineage dir creation,\n16: per-kind state-dir isolation, stdout capture, and orchestration artifacts.\n17: \n18: ### Why This Matters\n19: \n20: This is the script that dispatches all CLI executor fan-out lineages. If the per-kind\n21: `SPECKIT_<KIND>_STATE_DIR` is not set per-lineage, same-kind replicas collide on lockfiles.\n22: If stdout is not saved, the salvage sweep has nothing to recover from.\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n27: \n28: - Objective: Confirm `fanout-run.cjs` creates distinct per-lineage dirs and state dirs, writes orchestration artifacts, and returns early for native-only configs.\n29: - Layer partition: CLI lineage dispatch.\n30: - Real user request: `Validate the fan-out CLI lineage driver and confirm the 5 integration tests pass, verifying lineage isolation and orchestration artifact creation.`\n31: - Expected signals: `lineages/lineage-a/` and `lineages/lineage-b/` dirs created; `.executor-state/` paths distinct for same-kind replicas; `orchestration-summary.json` present with `total_cli_lineages=2`; `orchestration-status.log` has JSONL events; native-only config returns `{status:\"ok\", results:[]}`.\n32: - Pass/fail: PASS only if all 5 tests pass with EXIT 0 and source inspection confirms `SPECKIT_STATE_ENV_BY_KIND` usage; FAIL otherwise.\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n37: \n38: ### Prerequisites\n39: \n40: - Working directory is repository root.\n41: - `scripts/fanout-run.cjs` and `scripts/fanout-salvage.cjs` present.\n42: \n43: ### Steps\n44: \n45: 1. Inspect `scripts/fanout-run.cjs` — confirm `SPECKIT_STATE_ENV_BY_KIND` map, `computeLineageTimeoutMs` formula, `buildLineageCommand` per-kind branch.\n46: 2. Verify `extraEnv` in the worker sets both `SPECKIT_FANOUT_LINEAGE_ID` and the kind-specific state dir var.\n47: 3. `bash: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server && npx vitest run ../../runtime//tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts`\n48: 4. Confirm 5 tests pass. Note: the 2-lineage stub test verifies dirs, ledger, and summary; the lockfile-isolation test verifies `.executor-state` paths are distinct for same-kind replicas.\n49: \n50: ### Expected Outcome\n51: \n52: 5/5 pass. Lineage dirs created, `.executor-state` dirs distinct, `orchestration-summary.json` with `total_cli_lineages=2`, JSONL ledger written, native-only config returns early without spawning.\n53: \n54: ### Failure Modes\n55: \n56: - Missing `SPECKIT_<KIND>_STATE_DIR` in env: same-kind replicas use the same state dir and may trip the loop-lock.\n57: - stdout not saved to `logs/fanout-lineage.out`: salvage sweep has no data to recover from.\n58: - Pool worker throws instead of settling: pool fails entirely rather than reporting per-item status.\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## 4. SOURCE ANCHORS\n63: \n64: ### Implementation\n65: \n66: | File | Role |\n67: |---|---|\n68: | `scripts/fanout-run.cjs` | CLI arg parsing, pool orchestration, per-kind command construction, stdout capture, salvage call |\n69: | `scripts/fanout-salvage.cjs` | Salvage called in worker after subprocess exits |\n70: | `scripts/fanout-pool.cjs` | `runCappedPool` + ledger used by the driver |\n71: \n72: ### Validation\n73: \n74: | File | Role |\n75: |---|---|\n76: | `tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts` | 5 integration tests with stub CLI binaries |\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## 5. SOURCE_METADATA\n81: \n82: - Group: Fan-Out\n83: - Playbook ID: DLR-025\n84: - Feature catalog entry: `feature-catalog/fanout/fanout-run.md`\n85: - Scenario file path: `manual-testing-playbook/fanout/fanout-run-cli-lineage-spawn.md`\n86: - Expected verdict mode: GREEN when 5/5 pass and source anchors agree\n87: - Wall-time estimate: 5-10 min\n\n(End of file - total 87 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"DLR-025 -- Fan-out CLI lineage driver spawn and isolation\"\ndescription: \"Validate fanout-run.cjs creates per-lineage dirs with isolated .executor-state paths, saves stdout to logs/, writes orchestration summary and ledger, and returns early for native-only configs.\"\nversion: 1.4.0.4\n---\n\n# DLR-025 -- Fan-out CLI lineage driver spawn and isolation\n\nThis document captures the validation contract, execution flow, and metadata for `DLR-025`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nValidates the CLI lineage pool driver `fanout-run.cjs` — specifically lineage dir creation,\nper-kind state-dir isolation, stdout capture, and orchestration artifacts.\n\n### Why This Matters\n\nThis is the script that dispatches all CLI executor fan-out lineages. If the per-kind","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/manual-testing-playbook/fanout/fanout-run-cli-lineage-spawn.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"DLR-025 -- Fan-out CLI lineage driver spawn and isolation\"\ndescription: \"Validate fanout-run.cjs creates per-lineage dirs with isolated .executor-state paths, saves stdout to logs/, writes orchestration summary and ledger, and returns early for native-only configs.\"\nversion: 1.4.0.4\n---\n\n# DLR-025 -- Fan-out CLI lineage driver spawn and isolation\n\nThis document captures the validation contract, execution flow, and metadata for `DLR-025`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nValidates the CLI lineage pool driver `fanout-run.cjs` — specifically lineage dir creation,\nper-kind state-dir isolation, stdout capture, and orchestration artifacts.\n\n### Why This Matters\n\nThis is the script that dispatches all CLI executor fan-out lineages. If the per-kind\n`SPECKIT_<KIND>_STATE_DIR` is not set per-lineage, same-kind replicas collide on lockfiles.\nIf stdout is not saved, the salvage sweep has nothing to recover from.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\n- Objective: Confirm `fanout-run.cjs` creates distinct per-lineage dirs and state dirs, writes orchestration artifacts, and returns early for native-only configs.\n- Layer partition: CLI lineage dispatch.\n- Real user request: `Validate the fan-out CLI lineage driver and confirm the 5 integration tests pass, verifying lineage isolation and orchestration artifact creation.`\n- Expected signals: `lineages/lineage-a/` and `lineages/lineage-b/` dirs created; `.executor-state/` paths distinct for same-kind replicas; `orchestration-summary.json` present with `total_cli_lineages=2`; `orchestration-status.log` has JSONL events; native-only config returns `{status:\"ok\", results:[]}`.\n- Pass/fail: PASS only if all 5 tests pass with EXIT 0 and source inspection confirms `SPECKIT_STATE_ENV_BY_KIND` usage; FAIL otherwise.\n\n---\n\n## 3. TEST EXECUTION\n\n### Prerequisites\n\n- Working directory is repository root.\n- `scripts/fanout-run.cjs` and `scripts/fanout-salvage.cjs` present.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. Inspect `scripts/fanout-run.cjs` — confirm `SPECKIT_STATE_ENV_BY_KIND` map, `computeLineageTimeoutMs` formula, `buildLineageCommand` per-kind branch.\n2. Verify `extraEnv` in the worker sets both `SPECKIT_FANOUT_LINEAGE_ID` and the kind-specific state dir var.\n3. `bash: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server && npx vitest run ../../runtime//tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts`\n4. Confirm 5 tests pass. Note: the 2-lineage stub test verifies dirs, ledger, and summary; the lockfile-isolation test verifies `.executor-state` paths are distinct for same-kind replicas.\n\n### Expected Outcome\n\n5/5 pass. Lineage dirs created, `.executor-state` dirs distinct, `orchestration-summary.json` with `total_cli_lineages=2`, JSONL ledger written, native-only config returns early without spawning.\n\n### Failure Modes\n\n- Missing `SPECKIT_<KIND>_STATE_DIR` in env: same-kind replicas use the same state dir and may trip the loop-lock.\n- stdout not saved to `logs/fanout-lineage.out`: salvage sweep has no data to recover from.\n- Pool worker throws instead of settling: pool fails entirely rather than reporting per-item status.\n\n---\n\n## 4. SOURCE ANCHORS\n\n### Implementation\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `scripts/fanout-run.cjs` | CLI arg parsing, pool orchestration, per-kind command construction, stdout capture, salvage call |\n| `scripts/fanout-salvage.cjs` | Salvage called in worker after subprocess exits |\n| `scripts/fanout-pool.cjs` | `runCappedPool` + ledger used by the driver |\n\n### Validation\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts` | 5 integration tests with stub CLI binaries |\n\n---\n\n## 5. SOURCE_METADATA\n\n- Group: Fan-Out\n- Playbook ID: DLR-025\n- Feature catalog entry: `feature-catalog/fanout/fanout-run.md`\n- Scenario file path: `manual-testing-playbook/fanout/fanout-run-cli-lineage-spawn.md`\n- Expected verdict mode: GREEN when 5/5 pass and source anchors agree\n- Wall-time estimate: 5-10 min","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":87,"totalLines":87,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/manual-testing-playbook/fanout/fanout-run-cli-lineage-spawn.md","time":{"start":1784622868047,"end":1784622868093}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09e550be9e9f04eb016a5f2f13d710819196e24cd482ee4d8a"}},"id":"prt_f83cfe64b001Hsp9k8a7gZI2X6","sessionID":"ses_07c31cbc4ffeYIOJJ8ZhDDe6Fl","messageID":"msg_f83cf9fa3001SddLMGhg9tdoGl"}}
