{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784623030524,"sessionID":"ses_07c31cbc4ffeYIOJJ8ZhDDe6Fl","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9UqHv4GVnTlcaCa6ARFyzQSw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy: Styles SQLite Database Fate\n2: \n3: ## 1. Research Topic\n4: \n5: Decide whether to fully wire and populate the dormant styles SQLite database as the default retrieval path or formally shelve it and retain the flat-file engine as the single source.\n6: \n7: ## 2. Non-Goals\n8: \n9: - Do not implement, remove, rename, or relocate styles code or data.\n10: - Do not modify the parent spec packet or any path outside this detached lineage.\n11: - Do not decide the separate interface-command rewrite or styles-directory naming questions.\n12: - Do not treat code existence or passing unit tests alone as proof of production need.\n13: \n14: ## 3. Stop Conditions\n15: \n16: - Complete exactly five iterations because `stopPolicy=max-iterations`.\n17: - Produce an evidence-backed recommendation, decision framework, keep-path wiring plan, and shelf-path deprecation plan.\n18: - Ground the recommendation in the four design-mode corpus consumers and current operational evidence.\n19: \n20: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n21: ## 4. Key Questions (Remaining)\n22: \n23: - [ ] What contract and workload do design-interface, design-motion, design-audit, and design-foundations actually require from the styles library?\n24: - [ ] How complete is the persistent implementation, and what exact work remains to make it the default and populate a real database?\n25: - [ ] What measurable benefits justify SQLite at the present corpus size, and what recurring operational costs would default persistence introduce?\n26: - [ ] Which decision criteria and thresholds should govern keep versus shelve?\n27: - [ ] What are the safe wiring and deprecation plans, including rollback and preservation of useful evidence assets?\n28: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n29: \n30: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n31: ## 5. Answered Questions\n32: \n33: None yet.\n34: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n35: \n36: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n37: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n38: ## 6. What Worked\n39: \n40: None yet.\n41: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n42: \n43: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n44: ## 7. What Failed\n45: \n46: None yet.\n47: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n48: \n49: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n50: ## 8. Exhausted Approaches\n51: \n52: None yet.\n53: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n54: \n55: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n56: ## 9. Ruled-Out Directions\n57: \n58: None yet.\n59: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n60: \n61: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n62: ## 10. Carried-Forward Open Questions\n63: \n64: None yet.\n65: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n66: \n67: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n68: ## 11. Next Focus\n69: \n70: Map the actual design-mode consumer contract and runtime path before evaluating the storage implementation.\n71: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n72: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n73: \n74: ## 12. Known Context\n75: \n76: - The gap analysis reports 1,290 style folders, no SQLite file, a `legacy` default, and four corpus modules routed through `_engine/style-library.mjs`. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/gap-analysis.md:22-89]\n77: - The database foundation packet reports 69 passing tests for generation manifests, telemetry, differential oracle, fixtures, and judgments, but identifies live-corpus telemetry and human relevance labels as unresolved. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/015-styles-database-evolution/001-foundation/implementation-summary.md:50-57] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/015-styles-database-evolution/001-foundation/implementation-summary.md:117-123]\n78: - `resource-map.md` is not present in the target spec folder; skipping the input coverage gate.\n79: \n80: ## 13. Research Boundaries\n81: \n82: - Maximum iterations: 5\n83: - Stop policy: max-iterations\n84: - Convergence threshold: 0.05, telemetry only before iteration 5\n85: - Allowed write root: this detached `sol-high-fast` lineage only\n86: - Per-iteration write set: one prompt, one narrative, one delta, one state-log append, then workflow-owned reducer projections\n\n(End of file - total 86 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy: Styles SQLite Database Fate\n\n## 1. Research Topic\n\nDecide whether to fully wire and populate the dormant styles SQLite database as the default retrieval path or formally shelve it and retain the flat-file engine as the single source.\n\n## 2. Non-Goals\n\n- Do not implement, remove, rename, or relocate styles code or data.\n- Do not modify the parent spec packet or any path outside this detached lineage.\n- Do not decide the separate interface-command rewrite or styles-directory naming questions.\n- Do not treat code existence or passing unit tests alone as proof of production need.\n\n## 3. Stop Conditions\n\n- Complete exactly five iterations because `stopPolicy=max-iterations`.\n- Produce an evidence-backed recommendation, decision framework, keep-path wiring plan, and shelf-path deprecation plan.\n- Ground the recommendation in the four design-mode corpus consumers and current operational evidence.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy: Styles SQLite Database Fate\n\n## 1. Research Topic\n\nDecide whether to fully wire and populate the dormant styles SQLite database as the default retrieval path or formally shelve it and retain the flat-file engine as the single source.\n\n## 2. Non-Goals\n\n- Do not implement, remove, rename, or relocate styles code or data.\n- Do not modify the parent spec packet or any path outside this detached lineage.\n- Do not decide the separate interface-command rewrite or styles-directory naming questions.\n- Do not treat code existence or passing unit tests alone as proof of production need.\n\n## 3. Stop Conditions\n\n- Complete exactly five iterations because `stopPolicy=max-iterations`.\n- Produce an evidence-backed recommendation, decision framework, keep-path wiring plan, and shelf-path deprecation plan.\n- Ground the recommendation in the four design-mode corpus consumers and current operational evidence.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 4. Key Questions (Remaining)\n\n- [ ] What contract and workload do design-interface, design-motion, design-audit, and design-foundations actually require from the styles library?\n- [ ] How complete is the persistent implementation, and what exact work remains to make it the default and populate a real database?\n- [ ] What measurable benefits justify SQLite at the present corpus size, and what recurring operational costs would default persistence introduce?\n- [ ] Which decision criteria and thresholds should govern keep versus shelve?\n- [ ] What are the safe wiring and deprecation plans, including rollback and preservation of useful evidence assets?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 5. Answered Questions\n\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 6. What Worked\n\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 7. What Failed\n\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 8. Exhausted Approaches\n\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 9. Ruled-Out Directions\n\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 10. Carried-Forward Open Questions\n\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. Next Focus\n\nMap the actual design-mode consumer contract and runtime path before evaluating the storage implementation.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 12. Known Context\n\n- The gap analysis reports 1,290 style folders, no SQLite file, a `legacy` default, and four corpus modules routed through `_engine/style-library.mjs`. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/gap-analysis.md:22-89]\n- The database foundation packet reports 69 passing tests for generation manifests, telemetry, differential oracle, fixtures, and judgments, but identifies live-corpus telemetry and human relevance labels as unresolved. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/015-styles-database-evolution/001-foundation/implementation-summary.md:50-57] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/015-styles-database-evolution/001-foundation/implementation-summary.md:117-123]\n- `resource-map.md` is not present in the target spec folder; skipping the input coverage gate.\n\n## 13. Research Boundaries\n\n- Maximum iterations: 5\n- Stop policy: max-iterations\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05, telemetry only before iteration 5\n- Allowed write root: this detached `sol-high-fast` lineage only\n- Per-iteration write set: one prompt, one narrative, one delta, one state-log append, then workflow-owned reducer projections","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":86,"totalLines":86,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784623030514,"end":1784623030522}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0cadc0583aa8cdd0016a5f2fb5d60c81918ebe6f6f2bb03eb8"}},"id":"prt_f83d260e9001xbzDQl1J3F0dgW","sessionID":"ses_07c31cbc4ffeYIOJJ8ZhDDe6Fl","messageID":"msg_f83d20aba001JIYtUjEC7KI5ew"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784623030571,"sessionID":"ses_07c31cbc4ffeYIOJJ8ZhDDe6Fl","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_1eR1jzdl7ONCFy8LS1yQ99WD","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs","offset":1,"limit":270},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/usr/bin/env node\n2: // ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n3: // ║ Style Library CLI                                                       ║\n4: // ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n5: \n6: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n7: // 1. IMPORTS\n8: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n9: \n10: import { readFile } from 'node:fs/promises';\n11: import path from 'node:path';\n12: import { fileURLToPath, pathToFileURL } from 'node:url';\n13: \n14: import {\n15:   buildManifest,\n16:   diffManifests,\n17:   loadManifest,\n18:   serializeManifest,\n19:   writeManifestAtomic,\n20: } from './manifest.mjs';\n21: import { applyEligibility } from './eligibility.mjs';\n22: import { rankEligibleStyles } from './rank-fts.mjs';\n23: import { assembleCandidateCards } from './cards.mjs';\n24: import { bindHydrationManifest, hydrateBoundStyle } from './hydrate.mjs';\n25: import {\n26:   dispatchStyleHydrate,\n27:   dispatchStyleQuery,\n28: } from './persistent-adapter.mjs';\n29: \n30: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n31: // 2. CONSTANTS\n32: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n33: \n34: const ENGINE_ROOT = path.dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\n35: export const CORPUS_ROOT = path.resolve(ENGINE_ROOT, '..');\n36: export const MANIFEST_PATH = path.join(CORPUS_ROOT, '_retrieval-manifest.json');\n37: \n38: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n39: // 3. INPUT AND OUTPUT\n40: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n41: \n42: function writeJson(value, stream = process.stdout) {\n43:   stream.write(`${JSON.stringify(value, null, 2)}\\n`);\n44: }\n45: \n46: function optionValue(argumentsList, name) {\n47:   const index = argumentsList.indexOf(name);\n48:   return index === -1 ? null : argumentsList[index + 1] ?? null;\n49: }\n50: \n51: async function readStandardInput() {\n52:   if (process.stdin.isTTY) return '';\n53:   let input = '';\n54:   process.stdin.setEncoding('utf8');\n55:   for await (const chunk of process.stdin) input += chunk;\n56:   return input;\n57: }\n58: \n59: async function readRequest(argumentsList) {\n60:   const inline = optionValue(argumentsList, '--request');\n61:   if (inline) return JSON.parse(inline);\n62:   const requestFile = optionValue(argumentsList, '--file');\n63:   if (requestFile) return JSON.parse(await readFile(requestFile, 'utf8'));\n64:   const standardInput = await readStandardInput();\n65:   if (standardInput.trim()) return JSON.parse(standardInput);\n66:   return {};\n67: }\n68: \n69: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n70: // 4. BUILD COMMAND\n71: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n72: \n73: /**\n74:  * Build or check the canonical retrieval manifest.\n75:  *\n76:  * @param {string[]} argumentsList - Build flags.\n77:  * @param {Object} [options] - Overridable paths for isolated fixtures.\n78:  * @returns {Promise<{ok:boolean,mode:string,recordCount:number,diff:Object}>} Result summary.\n79:  */\n80: export async function runBuild(argumentsList, options = {}) {\n81:   const corpusRoot = options.corpusRoot ?? CORPUS_ROOT;\n82:   const manifestPath = options.manifestPath\n83:     ?? path.join(corpusRoot, '_retrieval-manifest.json');\n84:   const isWrite = argumentsList.includes('--write');\n85:   const isCheck = argumentsList.includes('--check');\n86:   if (isWrite === isCheck) {\n87:     const error = new Error('Build requires exactly one of --write or --check.');\n88:     error.code = 'invalid-arguments';\n89:     throw error;\n90:   }\n91: \n92:   const committed = await loadManifest(manifestPath, { corpusRoot });\n93:   const generated = await buildManifest(corpusRoot, {\n94:     previousManifest: isWrite ? committed : null,\n95:   });\n96:   const diff = diffManifests(committed, generated);\n97:   if (isWrite) {\n98:     await writeManifestAtomic(manifestPath, generated);\n99:     return { ok: true, mode: 'write', recordCount: generated.recordCount, diff };\n100:   }\n101: \n102:   let committedBytes = null;\n103:   try {\n104:     committedBytes = await readFile(manifestPath, 'utf8');\n105:   } catch (error) {\n106:     if (error.code !== 'ENOENT') throw error;\n107:   }\n108:   const ok = committedBytes === serializeManifest(generated);\n109:   return { ok, mode: 'check', recordCount: generated.recordCount, diff };\n110: }\n111: \n112: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n113: // 5. QUERY AND HYDRATE COMMANDS\n114: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n115: \n116: /**\n117:  * Apply deterministic membership before ranking and return compact cards.\n118:  *\n119:  * @param {Object} request - Generic retrieval request.\n120:  * @param {Object} [options] - Overridable paths for isolated fixtures.\n121:  * @returns {Promise<Object>} Query result with at most five eligible cards.\n122:  */\n123: async function runLegacyQuery(request, options = {}) {\n124:   const corpusRoot = options.corpusRoot ?? CORPUS_ROOT;\n125:   const manifestPath = options.manifestPath\n126:     ?? path.join(corpusRoot, '_retrieval-manifest.json');\n127:   const manifest = await loadManifest(manifestPath, { corpusRoot });\n128:   if (!manifest) {\n129:     const error = new Error('Retrieval manifest is missing. Run build --write first.');\n130:     error.code = 'manifest-missing';\n131:     throw error;\n132:   }\n133:   const liveManifest = await buildManifest(corpusRoot);\n134:   if (serializeManifest(liveManifest) !== serializeManifest(manifest)) {\n135:     const error = new Error('Retrieval manifest does not match the current corpus.');\n136:     error.code = 'manifest-stale';\n137:     throw error;\n138:   }\n139: \n140:   const eligibility = applyEligibility(manifest.styles, request);\n141:   const ranking = await rankEligibleStyles(eligibility.eligible, request, {\n142:     corpusRoot,\n143:     generationHash: manifest.generationHash,\n144:     useFts: request.useFts,\n145:     acceleratorGenerationHash: request.acceleratorGenerationHash,\n146:     scanLimits: options.scanLimits,\n147:   });\n148:   const cards = assembleCandidateCards(ranking.ranked, manifest.generationHash, request);\n149:   return {\n150:     ok: true,\n151:     generationHash: manifest.generationHash,\n152:     degraded: ranking.degraded,\n153:     rankingMode: ranking.rankingMode,\n154:     eligibility: {\n155:       eligibleCount: eligibility.eligible.length,\n156:       rejectedCount: eligibility.rejected.length,\n157:     },\n158:     cards,\n159:   };\n160: }\n161: \n162: /**\n163:  * Hydrate a selected card under the checked manifest and live generation guard.\n164:  *\n165:  * @param {Object} request - Hydration request.\n166:  * @param {Object} [options] - Overridable paths for isolated fixtures.\n167:  * @returns {Promise<Object>} Hydration result or refusal.\n168:  */\n169: async function runLegacyHydrate(request, options = {}) {\n170:   const corpusRoot = options.corpusRoot ?? CORPUS_ROOT;\n171:   const manifestPath = options.manifestPath\n172:     ?? path.join(corpusRoot, '_retrieval-manifest.json');\n173:   const manifest = await loadManifest(manifestPath, { corpusRoot });\n174:   if (!manifest) return { ok: false, error: 'manifest-missing' };\n175:   const bound = await bindHydrationManifest(manifest, request, { corpusRoot });\n176:   if (!bound.ok) return bound;\n177:   return hydrateBoundStyle(bound.binding, { corpusRoot });\n178: }\n179: \n180: /**\n181:  * Query through the legacy-default database migration adapter.\n182:  *\n183:  * @param {Object} request - Generic retrieval request.\n184:  * @param {Object} [options] - Paths and explicit adapter mode.\n185:  * @returns {Promise<Object>} Query result preserving the legacy card contract.\n186:  */\n187: export function runQuery(request, options = {}) {\n188:   return dispatchStyleQuery(\n189:     request,\n190:     { corpusRoot: options.corpusRoot ?? CORPUS_ROOT, ...options },\n191:     runLegacyQuery,\n192:   );\n193: }\n194: \n195: /**\n196:  * Hydrate through the legacy-default database migration adapter.\n197:  *\n198:  * @param {Object} request - Existing hydration request.\n199:  * @param {Object} [options] - Paths and explicit adapter mode.\n200:  * @returns {Promise<Object>} Existing hydration result or refusal.\n201:  */\n202: export function runHydrate(request, options = {}) {\n203:   return dispatchStyleHydrate(\n204:     request,\n205:     { corpusRoot: options.corpusRoot ?? CORPUS_ROOT, ...options },\n206:     runLegacyHydrate,\n207:   );\n208: }\n209: \n210: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n211: // 6. CLI DISPATCH\n212: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n213: \n214: /**\n215:  * Dispatch the style-library command line interface.\n216:  *\n217:  * @param {string[]} argumentsList - CLI arguments after the executable path.\n218:  * @returns {Promise<number>} Process exit code.\n219:  */\n220: export async function runCli(argumentsList = process.argv.slice(2)) {\n221:   const [command, ...commandArguments] = argumentsList;\n222:   if (command === 'build') {\n223:     const result = await runBuild(commandArguments);\n224:     writeJson(result);\n225:     return result.ok ? 0 : 1;\n226:   }\n227:   if (command === 'query') {\n228:     const result = await runQuery(await readRequest(commandArguments), {\n229:       styleDatabaseMode: optionValue(commandArguments, '--backend') ?? undefined,\n230:       databasePath: optionValue(commandArguments, '--database') ?? undefined,\n231:     });\n232:     writeJson(result);\n233:     return 0;\n234:   }\n235:   if (command === 'hydrate') {\n236:     const result = await runHydrate(await readRequest(commandArguments), {\n237:       styleDatabaseMode: optionValue(commandArguments, '--backend') ?? undefined,\n238:       databasePath: optionValue(commandArguments, '--database') ?? undefined,\n239:     });\n240:     writeJson(result);\n241:     return result.ok ? 0 : 1;\n242:   }\n243:   const error = new Error('Usage: style-library.mjs <build|query|hydrate> [options]');\n244:   error.code = 'invalid-arguments';\n245:   throw error;\n246: }\n247: \n248: const isDirectExecution = process.argv[1]\n249:   && import.meta.url === pathToFileURL(path.resolve(process.argv[1])).href;\n250: if (isDirectExecution) {\n251:   try {\n252:     process.exitCode = await runCli();\n253:   } catch (error) {\n254:     writeJson({\n255:       ok: false,\n256:       error: error.code ?? 'internal-error',\n257:       message: error.message,\n258:     }, process.stderr);\n259:     process.exitCode = 1;\n260:   }\n261: }\n\n(End of file - total 261 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Style Library CLI                                                       ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nimport { readFile } from 'node:fs/promises';\nimport path from 'node:path';\nimport { fileURLToPath, pathToFileURL } from 'node:url';\n\nimport {\n  buildManifest,\n  diffManifests,\n  loadManifest,\n  serializeManifest,\n  writeManifestAtomic,\n} from './manifest.mjs';","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs","text":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Style Library CLI                                                       ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nimport { readFile } from 'node:fs/promises';\nimport path from 'node:path';\nimport { fileURLToPath, pathToFileURL } from 'node:url';\n\nimport {\n  buildManifest,\n  diffManifests,\n  loadManifest,\n  serializeManifest,\n  writeManifestAtomic,\n} from './manifest.mjs';\nimport { applyEligibility } from './eligibility.mjs';\nimport { rankEligibleStyles } from './rank-fts.mjs';\nimport { assembleCandidateCards } from './cards.mjs';\nimport { bindHydrationManifest, hydrateBoundStyle } from './hydrate.mjs';\nimport {\n  dispatchStyleHydrate,\n  dispatchStyleQuery,\n} from './persistent-adapter.mjs';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 2. CONSTANTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst ENGINE_ROOT = path.dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\nexport const CORPUS_ROOT = path.resolve(ENGINE_ROOT, '..');\nexport const MANIFEST_PATH = path.join(CORPUS_ROOT, '_retrieval-manifest.json');\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 3. INPUT AND OUTPUT\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunction writeJson(value, stream = process.stdout) {\n  stream.write(`${JSON.stringify(value, null, 2)}\\n`);\n}\n\nfunction optionValue(argumentsList, name) {\n  const index = argumentsList.indexOf(name);\n  return index === -1 ? null : argumentsList[index + 1] ?? null;\n}\n\nasync function readStandardInput() {\n  if (process.stdin.isTTY) return '';\n  let input = '';\n  process.stdin.setEncoding('utf8');\n  for await (const chunk of process.stdin) input += chunk;\n  return input;\n}\n\nasync function readRequest(argumentsList) {\n  const inline = optionValue(argumentsList, '--request');\n  if (inline) return JSON.parse(inline);\n  const requestFile = optionValue(argumentsList, '--file');\n  if (requestFile) return JSON.parse(await readFile(requestFile, 'utf8'));\n  const standardInput = await readStandardInput();\n  if (standardInput.trim()) return JSON.parse(standardInput);\n  return {};\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 4. BUILD COMMAND\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * Build or check the canonical retrieval manifest.\n *\n * @param {string[]} argumentsList - Build flags.\n * @param {Object} [options] - Overridable paths for isolated fixtures.\n * @returns {Promise<{ok:boolean,mode:string,recordCount:number,diff:Object}>} Result summary.\n */\nexport async function runBuild(argumentsList, options = {}) {\n  const corpusRoot = options.corpusRoot ?? CORPUS_ROOT;\n  const manifestPath = options.manifestPath\n    ?? path.join(corpusRoot, '_retrieval-manifest.json');\n  const isWrite = argumentsList.includes('--write');\n  const isCheck = argumentsList.includes('--check');\n  if (isWrite === isCheck) {\n    const error = new Error('Build requires exactly one of --write or --check.');\n    error.code = 'invalid-arguments';\n    throw error;\n  }\n\n  const committed = await loadManifest(manifestPath, { corpusRoot });\n  const generated = await buildManifest(corpusRoot, {\n    previousManifest: isWrite ? committed : null,\n  });\n  const diff = diffManifests(committed, generated);\n  if (isWrite) {\n    await writeManifestAtomic(manifestPath, generated);\n    return { ok: true, mode: 'write', recordCount: generated.recordCount, diff };\n  }\n\n  let committedBytes = null;\n  try {\n    committedBytes = await readFile(manifestPath, 'utf8');\n  } catch (error) {\n    if (error.code !== 'ENOENT') throw error;\n  }\n  const ok = committedBytes === serializeManifest(generated);\n  return { ok, mode: 'check', recordCount: generated.recordCount, diff };\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 5. QUERY AND HYDRATE COMMANDS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * Apply deterministic membership before ranking and return compact cards.\n *\n * @param {Object} request - Generic retrieval request.\n * @param {Object} [options] - Overridable paths for isolated fixtures.\n * @returns {Promise<Object>} Query result with at most five eligible cards.\n */\nasync function runLegacyQuery(request, options = {}) {\n  const corpusRoot = options.corpusRoot ?? CORPUS_ROOT;\n  const manifestPath = options.manifestPath\n    ?? path.join(corpusRoot, '_retrieval-manifest.json');\n  const manifest = await loadManifest(manifestPath, { corpusRoot });\n  if (!manifest) {\n    const error = new Error('Retrieval manifest is missing. Run build --write first.');\n    error.code = 'manifest-missing';\n    throw error;\n  }\n  const liveManifest = await buildManifest(corpusRoot);\n  if (serializeManifest(liveManifest) !== serializeManifest(manifest)) {\n    const error = new Error('Retrieval manifest does not match the current corpus.');\n    error.code = 'manifest-stale';\n    throw error;\n  }\n\n  const eligibility = applyEligibility(manifest.styles, request);\n  const ranking = await rankEligibleStyles(eligibility.eligible, request, {\n    corpusRoot,\n    generationHash: manifest.generationHash,\n    useFts: request.useFts,\n    acceleratorGenerationHash: request.acceleratorGenerationHash,\n    scanLimits: options.scanLimits,\n  });\n  const cards = assembleCandidateCards(ranking.ranked, manifest.generationHash, request);\n  return {\n    ok: true,\n    generationHash: manifest.generationHash,\n    degraded: ranking.degraded,\n    rankingMode: ranking.rankingMode,\n    eligibility: {\n      eligibleCount: eligibility.eligible.length,\n      rejectedCount: eligibility.rejected.length,\n    },\n    cards,\n  };\n}\n\n/**\n * Hydrate a selected card under the checked manifest and live generation guard.\n *\n * @param {Object} request - Hydration request.\n * @param {Object} [options] - Overridable paths for isolated fixtures.\n * @returns {Promise<Object>} Hydration result or refusal.\n */\nasync function runLegacyHydrate(request, options = {}) {\n  const corpusRoot = options.corpusRoot ?? CORPUS_ROOT;\n  const manifestPath = options.manifestPath\n    ?? path.join(corpusRoot, '_retrieval-manifest.json');\n  const manifest = await loadManifest(manifestPath, { corpusRoot });\n  if (!manifest) return { ok: false, error: 'manifest-missing' };\n  const bound = await bindHydrationManifest(manifest, request, { corpusRoot });\n  if (!bound.ok) return bound;\n  return hydrateBoundStyle(bound.binding, { corpusRoot });\n}\n\n/**\n * Query through the legacy-default database migration adapter.\n *\n * @param {Object} request - Generic retrieval request.\n * @param {Object} [options] - Paths and explicit adapter mode.\n * @returns {Promise<Object>} Query result preserving the legacy card contract.\n */\nexport function runQuery(request, options = {}) {\n  return dispatchStyleQuery(\n    request,\n    { corpusRoot: options.corpusRoot ?? CORPUS_ROOT, ...options },\n    runLegacyQuery,\n  );\n}\n\n/**\n * Hydrate through the legacy-default database migration adapter.\n *\n * @param {Object} request - Existing hydration request.\n * @param {Object} [options] - Paths and explicit adapter mode.\n * @returns {Promise<Object>} Existing hydration result or refusal.\n */\nexport function runHydrate(request, options = {}) {\n  return dispatchStyleHydrate(\n    request,\n    { corpusRoot: options.corpusRoot ?? CORPUS_ROOT, ...options },\n    runLegacyHydrate,\n  );\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 6. CLI DISPATCH\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * Dispatch the style-library command line interface.\n *\n * @param {string[]} argumentsList - CLI arguments after the executable path.\n * @returns {Promise<number>} Process exit code.\n */\nexport async function runCli(argumentsList = process.argv.slice(2)) {\n  const [command, ...commandArguments] = argumentsList;\n  if (command === 'build') {\n    const result = await runBuild(commandArguments);\n    writeJson(result);\n    return result.ok ? 0 : 1;\n  }\n  if (command === 'query') {\n    const result = await runQuery(await readRequest(commandArguments), {\n      styleDatabaseMode: optionValue(commandArguments, '--backend') ?? undefined,\n      databasePath: optionValue(commandArguments, '--database') ?? undefined,\n    });\n    writeJson(result);\n    return 0;\n  }\n  if (command === 'hydrate') {\n    const result = await runHydrate(await readRequest(commandArguments), {\n      styleDatabaseMode: optionValue(commandArguments, '--backend') ?? undefined,\n      databasePath: optionValue(commandArguments, '--database') ?? undefined,\n    });\n    writeJson(result);\n    return result.ok ? 0 : 1;\n  }\n  const error = new Error('Usage: style-library.mjs <build|query|hydrate> [options]');\n  error.code = 'invalid-arguments';\n  throw error;\n}\n\nconst isDirectExecution = process.argv[1]\n  && import.meta.url === pathToFileURL(path.resolve(process.argv[1])).href;\nif (isDirectExecution) {\n  try {\n    process.exitCode = await runCli();\n  } catch (error) {\n    writeJson({\n      ok: false,\n      error: error.code ?? 'internal-error',\n      message: error.message,\n    }, process.stderr);\n    process.exitCode = 1;\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":261,"totalLines":261,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs","time":{"start":1784623030536,"end":1784623030569}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0cadc0583aa8cdd0016a5f2fb5d61481918d7d1f2e78a82665"}},"id":"prt_f83d260f4001SRRIKt8HEx0sl7","sessionID":"ses_07c31cbc4ffeYIOJJ8ZhDDe6Fl","messageID":"msg_f83d20aba001JIYtUjEC7KI5ew"}}
