esolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"run\":1,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Actual design-mode consumer contract and runtime path\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":1.0,\"noveltyJustification\":\"First iteration established five new contract-level findings from the actual consumers.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"What contract and workload do the four design-mode corpus consumers require?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"What contract and workload do the four design-mode corpus consumers require?\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"Consumer modules require a database-specific API\",\"SQLite would become the authoritative content store\",\"Consumer rewrites are required for backend selection\"],\"focusTrack\":\"architecture\",\"edgeCase\":\"ambiguous-input\",\"toolsUsed\":[\"Read\",\"Grep\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\"styles/_engine/style-library.mjs\",\"design-interface/corpus/relational-exemplar.mjs\",\"design-motion/corpus/motion-evidence.mjs\",\"design-audit/corpus/comparison-lane.mjs\",\"design-foundations/corpus/relationship-blueprint.mjs\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-21T08:38:00Z\",\"durationMs\":155000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784622756165-kgdopz\",\"generation\":1,\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\"},\"graphEvents\":[]}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"iteration\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-21T08:38:01Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784622756165-kgdopz\",\"generation\":1}\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -19,9 +19,9 @@\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n ## 4. Key Questions (Remaining)\n \n-- [ ] What contract and workload do design-interface, design-motion, design-audit, and design-foundations actually require from the styles library?\n+- [x] What contract and workload do design-interface, design-motion, design-audit, and design-foundations actually require from the styles library?\n - [ ] How complete is the persistent implementation, and what exact work remains to make it the default and populate a real database?\n - [ ] What measurable benefits justify SQLite at the present corpus size, and what recurring operational costs would default persistence introduce?\n - [ ] Which decision criteria and thresholds should govern keep versus shelve?\n - [ ] What are the safe wiring and deprecation plans, including rollback and preservation of useful evidence assets?\n@@ -29,28 +29,29 @@\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n ## 5. Answered Questions\n \n-None yet.\n+- The four consumers require a bounded, generation-safe `runQuery`/`runHydrate` facade and degrade safely when retrieval is unavailable; none requires SQLite specifically. (iteration 1)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n ## 6. What Worked\n \n-None yet.\n+- Consumer-to-facade tracing: showed that backend choice is isolated below all four corpus modules. (iteration 1)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 7. What Failed\n \n-None yet.\n+- Initial wildcard include search: returned no files because the path/include shape was too broad; replaced with an exact call-site search. (iteration 1)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n ## 8. Exhausted Approaches\n \n-None yet.\n+- Database-specific consumer rewrites: ruled out because all consumers already call the adapter-backed facade. (iteration 1)\n+- SQLite as authoritative content storage: ruled out because hydration remains flat-file artifact access. (iteration 1)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n ## 9. Ruled-Out Directions\n@@ -66,9 +67,9 @@\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. Next Focus\n \n-Map the actual design-mode consumer contract and runtime path before evaluating the storage implementation.\n+Assess persistent-backend completeness and enumerate the exact wiring/build work required for a real default database.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 12. Known Context\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n@@ -1,23 +1,31 @@\n {\n   \"openQuestions\": [\n-    {\"id\":\"q-consumers\",\"text\":\"What contract and workload do the four design-mode corpus consumers require?\",\"status\":\"open\"},\n     {\"id\":\"q-readiness\",\"text\":\"How complete is the persistent implementation and what remains to make it default?\",\"status\":\"open\"},\n     {\"id\":\"q-economics\",\"text\":\"What measurable benefits and recurring costs does SQLite introduce at current scale?\",\"status\":\"open\"},\n     {\"id\":\"q-criteria\",\"text\":\"Which decision criteria and thresholds govern keep versus shelve?\",\"status\":\"open\"},\n     {\"id\":\"q-plans\",\"text\":\"What are the safe wiring and deprecation plans?\",\"status\":\"open\"}\n   ],\n-  \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n-  \"keyFindings\": [],\n-  \"ruledOutDirections\": [],\n+  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n+    {\"id\":\"q-consumers\",\"text\":\"What contract and workload do the four design-mode corpus consumers require?\",\"status\":\"resolved\",\"resolvedAtIteration\":1,\"answer\":\"A bounded generation-safe query/hydration facade; no consumer requires SQLite specifically.\"}\n+  ],\n+  \"keyFindings\": [\n+    {\"id\":\"f-consumer-facade\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"All four corpus modules use the storage-neutral runQuery/runHydrate facade.\",\"sources\":[\"style-library.mjs:181-207\",\"four corpus modules\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"f-content-authority\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Flat artifacts remain authoritative content under persistent selection.\",\"sources\":[\"consumer hydration calls\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"f-legacy-freshness-cost\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Legacy queries rebuild and compare the live corpus manifest on every call.\",\"sources\":[\"style-library.mjs:123-159\"]}\n+  ],\n+  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n+    {\"approach\":\"Rewrite consumers for a database API\",\"reason\":\"The existing facade already isolates backend selection.\",\"iterations\":[1]},\n+    {\"approach\":\"Move authoritative content into SQLite\",\"reason\":\"Consumer hydration semantics rely on bounded flat artifacts.\",\"iterations\":[1]}\n+  ],\n   \"metrics\": {\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 0,\n-    \"openQuestions\": 5,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 0,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 0,\n-    \"convergenceScore\": 0,\n-    \"coverageBySources\": {}\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 1,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 4,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 1,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 3,\n+    \"convergenceScore\": 0.0,\n+    \"coverageBySources\": {\"code\":5,\"spec\":0,\"tests\":0}\n   },\n-  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n+  \"status\": \"iterating\",\n   \"sessionId\": \"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784622756165-kgdopz\",\n   \"generation\": 1\n }\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,26 @@\n+# Deep Research Dashboard\n+\n+## Iteration Table\n+\n+| Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n+|---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n+| 1 | Consumer contract and runtime path | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n+\n+## Question Status\n+\n+- 1/5 answered; 4 remaining.\n+- Answered: consumer contract and workload.\n+\n+## Convergence Trend\n+\n+- Ratios: 1.00\n+- Stop policy: max-iterations; convergence is telemetry until run 5.\n+\n+## Dead Ends\n+\n+- Database-specific consumer rewrites.\n+- SQLite as authoritative content storage.\n+\n+## Next Focus\n+\n+Persistent-backend completeness and missing wiring/build work.\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/research.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/research.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/research.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,15 @@\n+# Styles SQLite Database Fate: Progressive Research\n+\n+## Current Direction\n+\n+The decision should preserve the existing storage-neutral consumer facade. The four design modes require bounded generation-safe selection and flat-file hydration, not SQLite itself. [SOURCE: iteration-001.md]\n+\n+## Evidence Accumulated\n+\n+- All consumer modules use `runQuery`/`runHydrate` through `style-library.mjs`.\n+- Flat artifacts remain authoritative content under either backend.\n+- Legacy retrieval rebuilds and compares the live manifest on each query, creating the clearest potential benefit for a persistent index.\n+\n+## Open Decision\n+\n+Whether that avoidable per-query work and future retrieval capabilities outweigh build/publication/repair complexity at a 1,290-style corpus.\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/orchestration-status.log\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/orchestration-status.log\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/orchestration-status.log\n@@ -1,1 +1,2 @@\n {\"event\":\"started\",\"label\":\"sol-high-fast\",\"at\":\"2026-07-21T08:35:19Z\",\"duration_ms\":0,\"loop_type\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784622756165-kgdopz\",\"generation\":1,\"gauges\":{\"iterations\":0,\"elapsed_ms\":0,\"score\":0}}\n+{\"event\":\"progress\",\"label\":\"sol-high-fast\",\"at\":\"2026-07-21T08:38:01Z\",\"duration_ms\":162000,\"loop_type\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784622756165-kgdopz\",\"generation\":1,\"run\":1,\"status\":\"complete\",\"gauges\":{\"iterations\":1,\"elapsed_ms\":162000,\"score\":1.0}}\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/prompts/iteration-001.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/prompts/iteration-001.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/prompts/iteration-001.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/prompts/iteration-001.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/prompts/iteration-001.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,8 @@\n+DEEP-RESEARCH ITERATION 1\n+\n+STATE SUMMARY: Iteration 1 of 5; 0/5 questions answered; stop policy is max-iterations.\n+\n+Research Topic: Decide whether the dormant styles SQLite database should become the default or be formally shelved.\n+Focus Area: Map the actual design-mode consumer contract and runtime path.\n+Output: Write the iteration narrative, canonical state record, and delta inside this lineage only.\n+Route: mode=research; target_agent=deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files.\n","additions":8,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-001.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-001.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-001.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-001.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/iterations/iteration-001.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,55 @@\n+# Iteration 1: Actual Consumer Contract and Runtime Path\n+\n+## Focus\n+\n+Determine what the four design-mode corpus modules ask from the styles library and whether their contract inherently requires SQLite.\n+\n+## Findings\n+\n+1. All four consumers call the same storage-neutral `runQuery` and `runHydrate` facade. That facade delegates through `persistent-adapter.mjs`, so the consumer API already isolates backend choice; a keep or shelf decision need not change corpus-module call sites. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:181-207]\n+2. Every mode forces `usage: 'reference'`, `exactReuse: false`, and a bounded `limit`; the workloads are selection-oriented, not open-ended analytics or bulk traversal. Interface, motion, and foundations ultimately select specifically identified cards, while audit builds only zero to two comparisons. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/relational-exemplar.mjs:593-632] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/motion-evidence.mjs:752-822] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/comparison-lane.mjs:468-515] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/relationship-blueprint.mjs:818-867]\n+3. Generation identity is a hard semantic contract: every consumer rejects or degrades when `query.generationHash` differs from the context plan, and hydration repeats that generation hash. This favors preserving deterministic generation semantics, but not a specific storage technology. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/relational-exemplar.mjs:622-647] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/motion-evidence.mjs:808-822] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/comparison-lane.mjs:503-515] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/relationship-blueprint.mjs:854-875]\n+4. Hydration remains flat-file based even after database selection: consumers request bounded `DESIGN.md`, `source.md`, and sometimes `design-tokens.json` content by ID and generation. SQLite is therefore an index/select layer, not the authoritative content store. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/relational-exemplar.mjs:566-575] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/comparison-lane.mjs:448-457] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/relationship-blueprint.mjs:798-807]\n+5. The current legacy query pays a freshness cost on every call: it loads the committed manifest, rebuilds a live manifest from the corpus, byte-compares both, then performs eligibility/ranking/card assembly. SQLite could remove repeated corpus-walk work from normal reads, but only if its generation is built and published reliably. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:123-159]\n+\n+## Ruled Out\n+\n+- Treating the consumers as database-specific: their imported contract is the storage-neutral style-library facade.\n+- Treating SQLite as the content source: hydration still reads authoritative artifacts from the corpus.\n+\n+## Dead Ends\n+\n+- Rewriting the four design-mode modules as part of either option is unnecessary unless the response DTO changes, which the current adapter is designed to prevent.\n+\n+## Edge Cases\n+\n+- Ambiguous input: \"single source\" could mean metadata/index truth or content truth. This iteration distinguishes them: flat files remain content authority under both options.\n+- Contradictory evidence: none.\n+- Missing dependencies: none.\n+- Partial success: none.\n+\n+## Sources Consulted\n+\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:73-207`\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/corpus/relational-exemplar.mjs:535-659`\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/corpus/motion-evidence.mjs:700-834`\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/corpus/comparison-lane.mjs:420-539`\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/corpus/relationship-blueprint.mjs:770-899`\n+\n+## Assessment\n+\n+- New information ratio: 1.00\n+- Novelty justification: First iteration established five new contract-level findings from the actual consumers.\n+- Questions addressed: consumer contract and workload.\n+- Questions answered: the consumers need a bounded, generation-safe query/hydration facade, not SQLite specifically.\n+- Confidence: high for static runtime behavior; call frequency in real design sessions is not instrumented here.\n+\n+## Reflection\n+\n+- What worked and why: tracing all consumers to the shared facade exposed stable invariants without assuming storage needs.\n+- What did not work and why: repository-wide wildcard Grep did not accept the initial include shape; a narrower exact call-site search resolved it.\n+- What I would do differently: inspect adapter and database internals next, preserving the facade as the fixed boundary.\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+\n+Assess persistent-backend completeness: database opening, indexing/build, query parity, hydration behavior, publish/rollback, and the exact missing default-path wiring.\n","additions":55,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deltas/iter-001.jsonl","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deltas/iter-001.jsonl","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deltas/iter-001.jsonl\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deltas/iter-001.jsonl\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deltas/iter-001.jsonl\n@@ -0,0 +1,4 @@\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":1,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"run\":1,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Actual design-mode consumer contract and runtime path\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":1.0,\"noveltyJustification\":\"First iteration established five new contract-level findings from the actual consumers.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"What contract and workload do the four design-mode corpus consumers require?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"What contract and workload do the four design-mode corpus consumers require?\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"Consumer modules require a database-specific API\",\"SQLite would become the authoritative content store\",\"Consumer rewrites are required for backend selection\"],\"focusTrack\":\"architecture\",\"edgeCase\":\"ambiguous-input\",\"toolsUsed\":[\"Read\",\"Grep\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\"styles/_engine/style-library.mjs\",\"design-interface/corpus/relational-exemplar.mjs\",\"design-motion/corpus/motion-evidence.mjs\",\"design-audit/corpus/comparison-lane.mjs\",\"design-foundations/corpus/relationship-blueprint.mjs\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-21T08:38:00Z\",\"durationMs\":155000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784622756165-kgdopz\",\"generation\":1,\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\"},\"graphEvents\":[]}\n+{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-consumer-facade\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"All four corpus modules use the storage-neutral runQuery/runHydrate facade.\"}\n+{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-content-authority\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Flat artifacts remain authoritative content under persistent selection.\"}\n+{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-legacy-freshness-cost\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Legacy queries rebuild and compare the live corpus manifest on every call.\"}\n","additions":4,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-state.jsonl","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-state.jsonl","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-state.jsonl\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-state.jsonl\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-state.jsonl\n@@ -1,3 +1,5 @@\n {\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Decide whether to wire the dormant styles SQLite database into the default retrieval path or formally shelve it in favor of the flat-file engine\",\"maxIterations\":5,\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"antiConvergence\":{\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"stopPolicy\":\"max-iterations\",\"divergent\":{}},\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-21T08:35:03Z\",\"specFolder\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate\",\"artifactDir\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784622756165-kgdopz\",\"generation\":1,\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}\n {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"normalized_topic\":\"decide whether to wire the dormant styles sqlite database into the default retrieval path or formally shelve it in favor of the flat-file engine\",\"specPath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/.deep-research.lock\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-21T08:35:19Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784622756165-kgdopz\",\"generation\":1}\n {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_synthesis_deferred\",\"reason\":\"detached-lineage scope permits writes only inside the lineage artifact directory\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-21T08:35:19Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784622756165-kgdopz\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":1,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"run\":1,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Actual design-mode consumer contract and runtime path\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":1.0,\"noveltyJustification\":\"First iteration established five new contract-level findings from the actual consumers.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"What contract and workload do the four design-mode corpus consumers require?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"What contract and workload do the four design-mode corpus consumers require?\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"Consumer modules require a database-specific API\",\"SQLite would become the authoritative content store\",\"Consumer rewrites are required for backend selection\"],\"focusTrack\":\"architecture\",\"edgeCase\":\"ambiguous-input\",\"toolsUsed\":[\"Read\",\"Grep\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\"styles/_engine/style-library.mjs\",\"design-interface/corpus/relational-exemplar.mjs\",\"design-motion/corpus/motion-evidence.mjs\",\"design-audit/corpus/comparison-lane.mjs\",\"design-foundations/corpus/relationship-blueprint.mjs\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-21T08:38:00Z\",\"durationMs\":155000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784622756165-kgdopz\",\"generation\":1,\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast\"},\"graphEvents\":[]}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"iteration\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-21T08:38:01Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784622756165-kgdopz\",\"generation\":1}\n","additions":2,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -19,9 +19,9 @@\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n ## 4. Key Questions (Remaining)\n \n-- [ ] What contract and workload do design-interface, design-motion, design-audit, and design-foundations actually require from the styles library?\n+- [x] What contract and workload do design-interface, design-motion, design-audit, and design-foundations actually require from the styles library?\n - [ ] How complete is the persistent implementation, and what exact work remains to make it the default and populate a real database?\n - [ ] What measurable benefits justify SQLite at the present corpus size, and what recurring operational costs would default persistence introduce?\n - [ ] Which decision criteria and thresholds should govern keep versus shelve?\n - [ ] What are the safe wiring and deprecation plans, including rollback and preservation of useful evidence assets?\n@@ -29,28 +29,29 @@\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n ## 5. Answered Questions\n \n-None yet.\n+- The four consumers require a bounded, generation-safe `runQuery`/`runHydrate` facade and degrade safely when retrieval is unavailable; none requires SQLite specifically. (iteration 1)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n ## 6. What Worked\n \n-None yet.\n+- Consumer-to-facade tracing: showed that backend choice is isolated below all four corpus modules. (iteration 1)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 7. What Failed\n \n-None yet.\n+- Initial wildcard include search: returned no files because the path/include shape was too broad; replaced with an exact call-site search. (iteration 1)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n ## 8. Exhausted Approaches\n \n-None yet.\n+- Database-specific consumer rewrites: ruled out because all consumers already call the adapter-backed facade. (iteration 1)\n+- SQLite as authoritative content storage: ruled out because hydration remains flat-file artifact access. (iteration 1)\n <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n ## 9. Ruled-Out Directions\n@@ -66,9 +67,9 @@\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. Next Focus\n \n-Map the actual design-mode consumer contract and runtime path before evaluating the storage implementation.\n+Assess persistent-backend completeness and enumerate the exact wiring/build work required for a real default database.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 12. Known Context\n","additions":7,"deletions":6},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/findings-registry.json\n@@ -1,23 +1,31 @@\n {\n   \"openQuestions\": [\n-    {\"id\":\"q-consumers\",\"text\":\"What contract and workload do the four design-mode corpus consumers require?\",\"status\":\"open\"},\n     {\"id\":\"q-readiness\",\"text\":\"How complete is the persistent implementation and what remains to make it default?\",\"status\":\"open\"},\n     {\"id\":\"q-economics\",\"text\":\"What measurable benefits and recurring costs does SQLite introduce at current scale?\",\"status\":\"open\"},\n     {\"id\":\"q-criteria\",\"text\":\"Which decision criteria and thresholds govern keep versus shelve?\",\"status\":\"open\"},\n     {\"id\":\"q-plans\",\"text\":\"What are the safe wiring and deprecation plans?\",\"status\":\"open\"}\n   ],\n-  \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n-  \"keyFindings\": [],\n-  \"ruledOutDirections\": [],\n+  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n+    {\"id\":\"q-consumers\",\"text\":\"What contract and workload do the four design-mode corpus consumers require?\",\"status\":\"resolved\",\"resolvedAtIteration\":1,\"answer\":\"A bounded generation-safe query/hydration facade; no consumer requires SQLite specifically.\"}\n+  ],\n+  \"keyFindings\": [\n+    {\"id\":\"f-consumer-facade\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"All four corpus modules use the storage-neutral runQuery/runHydrate facade.\",\"sources\":[\"style-library.mjs:181-207\",\"four corpus modules\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"f-content-authority\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Flat artifacts remain authoritative content under persistent selection.\",\"sources\":[\"consumer hydration calls\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"f-legacy-freshness-cost\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Legacy queries rebuild and compare the live corpus manifest on every call.\",\"sources\":[\"style-library.mjs:123-159\"]}\n+  ],\n+  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n+    {\"approach\":\"Rewrite consumers for a database API\",\"reason\":\"The existing facade already isolates backend selection.\",\"iterations\":[1]},\n+    {\"approach\":\"Move authoritative content into SQLite\",\"reason\":\"Consumer hydration semantics rely on bounded flat artifacts.\",\"iterations\":[1]}\n+  ],\n   \"metrics\": {\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 0,\n-    \"openQuestions\": 5,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 0,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 0,\n-    \"convergenceScore\": 0,\n-    \"coverageBySources\": {}\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 1,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 4,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 1,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 3,\n+    \"convergenceScore\": 0.0,\n+    \"coverageBySources\": {\"code\":5,\"spec\":0,\"tests\":0}\n   },\n-  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n+  \"status\": \"iterating\",\n   \"sessionId\": \"fanout-sol-high-fast-1784622756165-kgdopz\",\n   \"generation\": 1\n }\n","additions":19,"deletions":11},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,26 @@\n+# Deep Research Dashboard\n+\n+## Iteration Table\n+\n+| Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n+|---:|---|---:|---:|---|\n+| 1 | Consumer contract and runtime path | 1.00 | 5 | complete |\n+\n+## Question Status\n+\n+- 1/5 answered; 4 remaining.\n+- Answered: consumer contract and workload.\n+\n+## Convergence Trend\n+\n+- Ratios: 1.00\n+- Stop policy: max-iterations; convergence is telemetry until run 5.\n+\n+## Dead Ends\n+\n+- Database-specific consumer rewrites.\n+- SQLite as authoritative content storage.\n+\n+## Next Focus\n+\n+Persistent-backend completeness and missing wiring/build work.\n","additions":26,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/research.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/research.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/research.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/research.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/research.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,15 @@\n+# Styles SQLite Database Fate: Progressive Research\n+\n+## Current Direction\n+\n+The decision should preserve the existing storage-neutral consumer facade. The four design modes require bounded generation-safe selection and flat-file hydration, not SQLite itself. [SOURCE: iteration-001.md]\n+\n+## Evidence Accumulated\n+\n+- All consumer modules use `runQuery`/`runHydrate` through `style-library.mjs`.\n+- Flat artifacts remain authoritative content under either backend.\n+- Legacy retrieval rebuilds and compares the live manifest on each query, creating the clearest potential benefit for a persistent index.\n+\n+## Open Decision\n+\n+Whether that avoidable per-query work and future retrieval capabilities outweigh build/publication/repair complexity at a 1,290-style corpus.\n","additions":15,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/orchestration-status.log","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/orchestration-status.log","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/orchestration-status.log\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-