{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784623544138,"sessionID":"ses_07c31cbc4ffeYIOJJ8ZhDDe6Fl","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_dnQrnwTlZSUBa9ytcZzIoWy2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy: Styles SQLite Database Fate\n2: \n3: ## 1. Research Topic\n4: \n5: Decide whether to fully wire and populate the dormant styles SQLite database as the default retrieval path or formally shelve it and retain the flat-file engine as the single source.\n6: \n7: ## 2. Non-Goals\n8: \n9: - Do not implement, remove, rename, or relocate styles code or data.\n10: - Do not modify the parent spec packet or any path outside this detached lineage.\n11: - Do not decide the separate interface-command rewrite or styles-directory naming questions.\n12: - Do not treat code existence or passing unit tests alone as proof of production need.\n13: \n14: ## 3. Stop Conditions\n15: \n16: - Complete exactly five iterations because `stopPolicy=max-iterations`.\n17: - Produce an evidence-backed recommendation, decision framework, keep-path wiring plan, and shelf-path deprecation plan.\n18: - Ground the recommendation in the four design-mode corpus consumers and current operational evidence.\n19: \n20: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n21: ## 4. Key Questions (Remaining)\n22: \n23: - [x] What contract and workload do design-interface, design-motion, design-audit, and design-foundations actually require from the styles library?\n24: - [x] How complete is the persistent implementation, and what exact work remains to make it the default and populate a real database?\n25: - [x] What measurable benefits justify SQLite at the present corpus size, and what recurring operational costs would default persistence introduce?\n26: - [x] Which decision criteria and thresholds should govern keep versus shelve?\n27: - [ ] What are the safe wiring and deprecation plans, including rollback and preservation of useful evidence assets?\n28: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n29: \n30: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n31: ## 5. Answered Questions\n32: \n33: - The four consumers require a bounded, generation-safe `runQuery`/`runHydrate` facade and degrade safely when retrieval is unavailable; none requires SQLite specifically. (iteration 1)\n34: - The persistent implementation is mature, but a real default requires a published initial generation plus explicit build/distribution/refresh/repair ownership and live cutover evidence. (iteration 2)\n35: - Persistent selection avoids substantial repeat-query corpus I/O, but the only direct speed assertion is a 20-style fixture; present-scale materiality, workload demand, relevance quality, and lifecycle cost remain unmeasured. (iteration 3)\n36: - A weighted present-state framework scores formal shelving 85/100 versus wiring 54/100; reversal requires conjunctive workload, materiality, lifecycle, parity, relevance, shadow, rollback, and demand gates. (iteration 4)\n37: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n38: \n39: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n40: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n41: ## 6. What Worked\n42: \n43: - Consumer-to-facade tracing: showed that backend choice is isolated below all four corpus modules. (iteration 1)\n44: - Implementation-versus-integration separation: distinguished mature database code from the absent operational lifecycle. (iteration 2)\n45: - Evidence-class separation: distinguished correctness, directional speed, material speed, and product demand. (iteration 3)\n46: - Weighted scoring and sensitivity check: made judgment explicit and showed the result is not dependent on one criterion. (iteration 4)\n47: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n48: \n49: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n50: ## 7. What Failed\n51: \n52: - Initial wildcard include search: returned no files because the path/include shape was too broad; replaced with an exact call-site search. (iteration 1)\n53: - First-segment indexer read: did not reach the build function, so operator and README evidence were used to triangulate the published lifecycle. (iteration 2)\n54: - Exact ROI modeling: blocked by the absent full-corpus database, workload trace, build timing, and human relevance set. (iteration 3)\n55: - Broad feature-token search: included database internals, so its absence claim was narrowed to consumer call sites. (iteration 4)\n56: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n57: \n58: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n59: ## 8. Exhausted Approaches\n60: \n61: - Database-specific consumer rewrites: ruled out because all consumers already call the adapter-backed facade. (iteration 1)\n62: - SQLite as authoritative content storage: ruled out because hydration remains flat-file artifact access. (iteration 1)\n63: - Default flip without build/distribution: ruled out because clean checkouts have no pointer or generation file. (iteration 2)\n64: - Capability inventory as business justification: ruled out because consumer demand and measured value are separate. (iteration 2)\n65: - Synthetic 20-style timing as production justification: ruled out because it proves direction but records no materiality. (iteration 3)\n66: - Correctness suite as demand proof: ruled out because safety and usefulness are separate questions. (iteration 3)\n67: - Dormant-code optionality: ruled out because Git history and decision evidence preserve recovery without active runtime ownership. (iteration 4)\n68: - Sunk-cost promotion and one-benchmark promotion: ruled out by conjunctive promotion gates. (iteration 4)\n69: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n70: \n71: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n72: ## 9. Ruled-Out Directions\n73: \n74: None yet.\n75: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n76: \n77: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n78: ## 10. Carried-Forward Open Questions\n79: \n80: None yet.\n81: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n82: \n83: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n84: ## 11. Next Focus\n85: \n86: Adversarially validate the shelf recommendation and produce complete wiring and deprecation plans with rollback and roadmap consequences.\n87: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n88: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n89: \n90: ## 12. Known Context\n91: \n92: - The gap analysis reports 1,290 style folders, no SQLite file, a `legacy` default, and four corpus modules routed through `_engine/style-library.mjs`. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/gap-analysis.md:22-89]\n93: - The database foundation packet reports 69 passing tests for generation manifests, telemetry, differential oracle, fixtures, and judgments, but identifies live-corpus telemetry and human relevance labels as unresolved. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/015-styles-database-evolution/001-foundation/implementation-summary.md:50-57] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/015-styles-database-evolution/001-foundation/implementation-summary.md:117-123]\n94: - `resource-map.md` is not present in the target spec folder; skipping the input coverage gate.\n95: \n96: ## 13. Research Boundaries\n97: \n98: - Maximum iterations: 5\n99: - Stop policy: max-iterations\n100: - Convergence threshold: 0.05, telemetry only before iteration 5\n101: - Allowed write root: this detached `sol-high-fast` lineage only\n102: - Per-iteration write set: one prompt, one narrative, one delta, one state-log append, then workflow-owned reducer projections\n\n(End of file - total 102 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy: Styles SQLite Database Fate\n\n## 1. Research Topic\n\nDecide whether to fully wire and populate the dormant styles SQLite database as the default retrieval path or formally shelve it and retain the flat-file engine as the single source.\n\n## 2. Non-Goals\n\n- Do not implement, remove, rename, or relocate styles code or data.\n- Do not modify the parent spec packet or any path outside this detached lineage.\n- Do not decide the separate interface-command rewrite or styles-directory naming questions.\n- Do not treat code existence or passing unit tests alone as proof of production need.\n\n## 3. Stop Conditions\n\n- Complete exactly five iterations because `stopPolicy=max-iterations`.\n- Produce an evidence-backed recommendation, decision framework, keep-path wiring plan, and shelf-path deprecation plan.\n- Ground the recommendation in the four design-mode corpus consumers and current operational evidence.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy: Styles SQLite Database Fate\n\n## 1. Research Topic\n\nDecide whether to fully wire and populate the dormant styles SQLite database as the default retrieval path or formally shelve it and retain the flat-file engine as the single source.\n\n## 2. Non-Goals\n\n- Do not implement, remove, rename, or relocate styles code or data.\n- Do not modify the parent spec packet or any path outside this detached lineage.\n- Do not decide the separate interface-command rewrite or styles-directory naming questions.\n- Do not treat code existence or passing unit tests alone as proof of production need.\n\n## 3. Stop Conditions\n\n- Complete exactly five iterations because `stopPolicy=max-iterations`.\n- Produce an evidence-backed recommendation, decision framework, keep-path wiring plan, and shelf-path deprecation plan.\n- Ground the recommendation in the four design-mode corpus consumers and current operational evidence.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 4. Key Questions (Remaining)\n\n- [x] What contract and workload do design-interface, design-motion, design-audit, and design-foundations actually require from the styles library?\n- [x] How complete is the persistent implementation, and what exact work remains to make it the default and populate a real database?\n- [x] What measurable benefits justify SQLite at the present corpus size, and what recurring operational costs would default persistence introduce?\n- [x] Which decision criteria and thresholds should govern keep versus shelve?\n- [ ] What are the safe wiring and deprecation plans, including rollback and preservation of useful evidence assets?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 5. Answered Questions\n\n- The four consumers require a bounded, generation-safe `runQuery`/`runHydrate` facade and degrade safely when retrieval is unavailable; none requires SQLite specifically. (iteration 1)\n- The persistent implementation is mature, but a real default requires a published initial generation plus explicit build/distribution/refresh/repair ownership and live cutover evidence. (iteration 2)\n- Persistent selection avoids substantial repeat-query corpus I/O, but the only direct speed assertion is a 20-style fixture; present-scale materiality, workload demand, relevance quality, and lifecycle cost remain unmeasured. (iteration 3)\n- A weighted present-state framework scores formal shelving 85/100 versus wiring 54/100; reversal requires conjunctive workload, materiality, lifecycle, parity, relevance, shadow, rollback, and demand gates. (iteration 4)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 6. What Worked\n\n- Consumer-to-facade tracing: showed that backend choice is isolated below all four corpus modules. (iteration 1)\n- Implementation-versus-integration separation: distinguished mature database code from the absent operational lifecycle. (iteration 2)\n- Evidence-class separation: distinguished correctness, directional speed, material speed, and product demand. (iteration 3)\n- Weighted scoring and sensitivity check: made judgment explicit and showed the result is not dependent on one criterion. (iteration 4)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 7. What Failed\n\n- Initial wildcard include search: returned no files because the path/include shape was too broad; replaced with an exact call-site search. (iteration 1)\n- First-segment indexer read: did not reach the build function, so operator and README evidence were used to triangulate the published lifecycle. (iteration 2)\n- Exact ROI modeling: blocked by the absent full-corpus database, workload trace, build timing, and human relevance set. (iteration 3)\n- Broad feature-token search: included database internals, so its absence claim was narrowed to consumer call sites. (iteration 4)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 8. Exhausted Approaches\n\n- Database-specific consumer rewrites: ruled out because all consumers already call the adapter-backed facade. (iteration 1)\n- SQLite as authoritative content storage: ruled out because hydration remains flat-file artifact access. (iteration 1)\n- Default flip without build/distribution: ruled out because clean checkouts have no pointer or generation file. (iteration 2)\n- Capability inventory as business justification: ruled out because consumer demand and measured value are separate. (iteration 2)\n- Synthetic 20-style timing as production justification: ruled out because it proves direction but records no materiality. (iteration 3)\n- Correctness suite as demand proof: ruled out because safety and usefulness are separate questions. (iteration 3)\n- Dormant-code optionality: ruled out because Git history and decision evidence preserve recovery without active runtime ownership. (iteration 4)\n- Sunk-cost promotion and one-benchmark promotion: ruled out by conjunctive promotion gates. (iteration 4)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 9. Ruled-Out Directions\n\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 10. Carried-Forward Open Questions\n\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. Next Focus\n\nAdversarially validate the shelf recommendation and produce complete wiring and deprecation plans with rollback and roadmap consequences.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 12. Known Context\n\n- The gap analysis reports 1,290 style folders, no SQLite file, a `legacy` default, and four corpus modules routed through `_engine/style-library.mjs`. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/gap-analysis.md:22-89]\n- The database foundation packet reports 69 passing tests for generation manifests, telemetry, differential oracle, fixtures, and judgments, but identifies live-corpus telemetry and human relevance labels as unresolved. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/015-styles-database-evolution/001-foundation/implementation-summary.md:50-57] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/sk-design/015-styles-database-evolution/001-foundation/implementation-summary.md:117-123]\n- `resource-map.md` is not present in the target spec folder; skipping the input coverage gate.\n\n## 13. Research Boundaries\n\n- Maximum iterations: 5\n- Stop policy: max-iterations\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05, telemetry only before iteration 5\n- Allowed write root: this detached `sol-high-fast` lineage only\n- Per-iteration write set: one prompt, one narrative, one delta, one state-log append, then workflow-owned reducer projections","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":102,"totalLines":102,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/007-gap-remediation-research/003-db-fate/research/lineages/sol-high-fast/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784623544013,"end":1784623544135}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_079baf33226c216e016a5f31b7c938819196b874831777c5ad"}},"id":"prt_f83da36b9001Vm9eKypThD6nWt","sessionID":"ses_07c31cbc4ffeYIOJJ8ZhDDe6Fl","messageID":"msg_f83d9c457001dsEnL1Wkw9V761"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784623544149,"sessionID":"ses_07c31cbc4ffeYIOJJ8ZhDDe6Fl","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_syVaAfQeIqGJe1PM0Ix6FIg8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/check-stable.test.mjs","offset":1,"limit":180},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/check-stable.test.mjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n2: // ║ Stable Manifest Check Fixture                                           ║\n3: // ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n4: \n5: import assert from 'node:assert/strict';\n6: import { spawnSync } from 'node:child_process';\n7: import { readFile, writeFile } from 'node:fs/promises';\n8: import path from 'node:path';\n9: import test from 'node:test';\n10: \n11: import { runBuild, runQuery } from '../style-library.mjs';\n12: import { STYLE_ALPHA, createFixtureCorpus } from './fixtures.mjs';\n13: \n14: test('build --check is byte-stable and never writes', async (context) => {\n15:   const fixture = await createFixtureCorpus();\n16:   context.after(fixture.cleanup);\n17:   const manifestPath = path.join(fixture.root, '_retrieval-manifest.json');\n18:   const written = await runBuild(['--write'], { corpusRoot: fixture.root, manifestPath });\n19:   assert.equal(written.ok, true);\n20:   const firstBytes = await readFile(manifestPath, 'utf8');\n21:   const firstCheck = await runBuild(['--check'], { corpusRoot: fixture.root, manifestPath });\n22:   const secondCheck = await runBuild(['--check'], { corpusRoot: fixture.root, manifestPath });\n23:   assert.equal(firstCheck.ok, true);\n24:   assert.equal(secondCheck.ok, true);\n25:   assert.deepEqual(secondCheck.diff, { added: [], changed: [], removed: [] });\n26:   assert.equal(await readFile(manifestPath, 'utf8'), firstBytes);\n27: });\n28: \n29: test('build --check is byte-stable under a Turkish process locale', async (context) => {\n30:   const fixture = await createFixtureCorpus();\n31:   context.after(fixture.cleanup);\n32:   const manifestPath = path.join(fixture.root, '_retrieval-manifest.json');\n33:   await runBuild(['--write'], { corpusRoot: fixture.root, manifestPath });\n34:   const committedBytes = await readFile(manifestPath, 'utf8');\n35:   const moduleUrl = new URL('../style-library.mjs', import.meta.url).href;\n36:   const script = `\n37:     import { runBuild } from ${JSON.stringify(moduleUrl)};\n38:     const result = await runBuild(['--check'], {\n39:       corpusRoot: ${JSON.stringify(fixture.root)},\n40:       manifestPath: ${JSON.stringify(manifestPath)},\n41:     });\n42:     process.stdout.write(JSON.stringify(result));\n43:     process.exitCode = result.ok ? 0 : 1;\n44:   `;\n45:   const child = spawnSync(process.execPath, ['--input-type=module', '--eval', script], {\n46:     encoding: 'utf8',\n47:     env: { ...process.env, LC_ALL: 'tr_TR.UTF-8', LANG: 'tr_TR.UTF-8' },\n48:   });\n49:   assert.equal(child.status, 0, child.stderr || child.stdout);\n50:   assert.equal(JSON.parse(child.stdout).ok, true);\n51:   assert.equal(await readFile(manifestPath, 'utf8'), committedBytes);\n52: });\n53: \n54: test('build --check rejects poisoned derived fields with unchanged source hashes', async (context) => {\n55:   const fixture = await createFixtureCorpus();\n56:   context.after(fixture.cleanup);\n57:   const manifestPath = path.join(fixture.root, '_retrieval-manifest.json');\n58:   await runBuild(['--write'], { corpusRoot: fixture.root, manifestPath });\n59:   const poisoned = JSON.parse(await readFile(manifestPath, 'utf8'));\n60:   const record = poisoned.styles.find((style) => style.id === STYLE_ALPHA.id);\n61:   const contentHash = record.contentHash;\n62:   record.facets = ['motion', 'poisoned'];\n63:   record.provenance.licenseStatus = 'licensed';\n64:   record.provenance.rightsKnown = true;\n65:   await writeFile(manifestPath, `${JSON.stringify(poisoned, null, 2)}\\n`);\n66: \n67:   const checked = await runBuild(['--check'], { corpusRoot: fixture.root, manifestPath });\n68:   assert.equal(checked.ok, false);\n69:   assert.deepEqual(checked.diff.changed, [STYLE_ALPHA.id]);\n70:   const persisted = JSON.parse(await readFile(manifestPath, 'utf8'));\n71:   assert.equal(persisted.styles.find((style) => style.id === STYLE_ALPHA.id).contentHash, contentHash);\n72:   assert.deepEqual(\n73:     persisted.styles.find((style) => style.id === STYLE_ALPHA.id).facets,\n74:     ['motion', 'poisoned'],\n75:   );\n76:   await assert.rejects(\n77:     runQuery({}, { corpusRoot: fixture.root, manifestPath }),\n78:     (error) => error.code === 'manifest-stale',\n79:   );\n80: });\n\n(End of file - total 80 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Stable Manifest Check Fixture                                           ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\nimport assert from 'node:assert/strict';\nimport { spawnSync } from 'node:child_process';\nimport { readFile, writeFile } from 'node:fs/promises';\nimport path from 'node:path';\nimport test from 'node:test';\n\nimport { runBuild, runQuery } from '../style-library.mjs';\nimport { STYLE_ALPHA, createFixtureCorpus } from './fixtures.mjs';\n\ntest('build --check is byte-stable and never writes', async (context) => {\n  const fixture = await createFixtureCorpus();\n  context.after(fixture.cleanup);\n  const manifestPath = path.join(fixture.root, '_retrieval-manifest.json');\n  const written = await runBuild(['--write'], { corpusRoot: fixture.root, manifestPath });\n  assert.equal(written.ok, true);\n  const firstBytes = await readFile(manifestPath, 'utf8');","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/check-stable.test.mjs","text":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Stable Manifest Check Fixture                                           ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\nimport assert from 'node:assert/strict';\nimport { spawnSync } from 'node:child_process';\nimport { readFile, writeFile } from 'node:fs/promises';\nimport path from 'node:path';\nimport test from 'node:test';\n\nimport { runBuild, runQuery } from '../style-library.mjs';\nimport { STYLE_ALPHA, createFixtureCorpus } from './fixtures.mjs';\n\ntest('build --check is byte-stable and never writes', async (context) => {\n  const fixture = await createFixtureCorpus();\n  context.after(fixture.cleanup);\n  const manifestPath = path.join(fixture.root, '_retrieval-manifest.json');\n  const written = await runBuild(['--write'], { corpusRoot: fixture.root, manifestPath });\n  assert.equal(written.ok, true);\n  const firstBytes = await readFile(manifestPath, 'utf8');\n  const firstCheck = await runBuild(['--check'], { corpusRoot: fixture.root, manifestPath });\n  const secondCheck = await runBuild(['--check'], { corpusRoot: fixture.root, manifestPath });\n  assert.equal(firstCheck.ok, true);\n  assert.equal(secondCheck.ok, true);\n  assert.deepEqual(secondCheck.diff, { added: [], changed: [], removed: [] });\n  assert.equal(await readFile(manifestPath, 'utf8'), firstBytes);\n});\n\ntest('build --check is byte-stable under a Turkish process locale', async (context) => {\n  const fixture = await createFixtureCorpus();\n  context.after(fixture.cleanup);\n  const manifestPath = path.join(fixture.root, '_retrieval-manifest.json');\n  await runBuild(['--write'], { corpusRoot: fixture.root, manifestPath });\n  const committedBytes = await readFile(manifestPath, 'utf8');\n  const moduleUrl = new URL('../style-library.mjs', import.meta.url).href;\n  const script = `\n    import { runBuild } from ${JSON.stringify(moduleUrl)};\n    const result = await runBuild(['--check'], {\n      corpusRoot: ${JSON.stringify(fixture.root)},\n      manifestPath: ${JSON.stringify(manifestPath)},\n    });\n    process.stdout.write(JSON.stringify(result));\n    process.exitCode = result.ok ? 0 : 1;\n  `;\n  const child = spawnSync(process.execPath, ['--input-type=module', '--eval', script], {\n    encoding: 'utf8',\n    env: { ...process.env, LC_ALL: 'tr_TR.UTF-8', LANG: 'tr_TR.UTF-8' },\n  });\n  assert.equal(child.status, 0, child.stderr || child.stdout);\n  assert.equal(JSON.parse(child.stdout).ok, true);\n  assert.equal(await readFile(manifestPath, 'utf8'), committedBytes);\n});\n\ntest('build --check rejects poisoned derived fields with unchanged source hashes', async (context) => {\n  const fixture = await createFixtureCorpus();\n  context.after(fixture.cleanup);\n  const manifestPath = path.join(fixture.root, '_retrieval-manifest.json');\n  await runBuild(['--write'], { corpusRoot: fixture.root, manifestPath });\n  const poisoned = JSON.parse(await readFile(manifestPath, 'utf8'));\n  const record = poisoned.styles.find((style) => style.id === STYLE_ALPHA.id);\n  const contentHash = record.contentHash;\n  record.facets = ['motion', 'poisoned'];\n  record.provenance.licenseStatus = 'licensed';\n  record.provenance.rightsKnown = true;\n  await writeFile(manifestPath, `${JSON.stringify(poisoned, null, 2)}\\n`);\n\n  const checked = await runBuild(['--check'], { corpusRoot: fixture.root, manifestPath });\n  assert.equal(checked.ok, false);\n  assert.deepEqual(checked.diff.changed, [STYLE_ALPHA.id]);\n  const persisted = JSON.parse(await readFile(manifestPath, 'utf8'));\n  assert.equal(persisted.styles.find((style) => style.id === STYLE_ALPHA.id).contentHash, contentHash);\n  assert.deepEqual(\n    persisted.styles.find((style) => style.id === STYLE_ALPHA.id).facets,\n    ['motion', 'poisoned'],\n  );\n  await assert.rejects(\n    runQuery({}, { corpusRoot: fixture.root, manifestPath }),\n    (error) => error.code === 'manifest-stale',\n  );\n});","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":80,"totalLines":80,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/check-stable.test.mjs","time":{"start":1784623544040,"end":1784623544139}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_079baf33226c216e016a5f31b7c9588191b10e73ec209c8b3f"}},"id":"prt_f83da36e6001W4ExxU3w4hih4O","sessionID":"ses_07c31cbc4ffeYIOJJ8ZhDDe6Fl","messageID":"msg_f83d9c457001dsEnL1Wkw9V761"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784623544149,"sessionID":"ses_07c31cbc4ffeYIOJJ8ZhDDe6Fl","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_TpHkBruYuXnLHg1ZJsbYXZlK","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/index.mjs","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/index.mjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n2: // ║ Legacy Style Engine Test Suite                                           ║\n3: // ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n4: \n5: import './check-stable.test.mjs';\n6: import './eligibility-first.test.mjs';\n7: import './fallback.test.mjs';\n8: import './hydrate-guard.test.mjs';\n9: import './invalidation.test.mjs';\n10: import './proof.test.mjs';\n\n(End of file - total 10 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Legacy Style Engine Test Suite                                           ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\nimport './check-stable.test.mjs';\nimport './eligibility-first.test.mjs';\nimport './fallback.test.mjs';\nimport './hydrate-guard.test.mjs';\nimport './invalidation.test.mjs';\nimport './proof.test.mjs';","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/index.mjs","text":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Legacy Style Engine Test Suite                                           ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\nimport './check-stable.test.mjs';\nimport './eligibility-first.test.mjs';\nimport './fallback.test.mjs';\nimport './hydrate-guard.test.mjs';\nimport './invalidation.test.mjs';\nimport './proof.test.mjs';","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":10,"totalLines":10,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/index.mjs","time":{"start":1784623544036,"end":1784623544143}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_079baf33226c216e016a5f31b7c9508191b5bb15d72aa50f55"}},"id":"prt_f83da36de001pdbmR4wDJe29Mz","sessionID":"ses_07c31cbc4ffeYIOJJ8ZhDDe6Fl","messageID":"msg_f83d9c457001dsEnL1Wkw9V761"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784623544149,"sessionID":"ses_07c31cbc4ffeYIOJJ8ZhDDe6Fl","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_EJJvAX4Ycb3tpt5WrtqmvAuo","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/hydrate-guard.test.mjs","offset":1,"limit":180},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/hydrate-guard.test.mjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n2: // ║ Hydration Generation and Path Guards                                    ║\n3: // ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n4: \n5: import assert from 'node:assert/strict';\n6: import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n7: import { mkdir, readFile, symlink, writeFile } from 'node:fs/promises';\n8: import path from 'node:path';\n9: import test from 'node:test';\n10: \n11: import { bindHydrationManifest, hydrateStyle } from '../hydrate.mjs';\n12: import { buildManifest } from '../manifest.mjs';\n13: import { runBuild, runHydrate } from '../style-library.mjs';\n14: import { STYLE_ALPHA, STYLE_BETA, createFixtureCorpus } from './fixtures.mjs';\n15: \n16: function artifactDigest(content) {\n17:   return `sha256:${createHash('sha256').update(content).digest('hex')}`;\n18: }\n19: \n20: test('hydration refuses a stale generation and honors byte caps', async (context) => {\n21:   const fixture = await createFixtureCorpus();\n22:   context.after(fixture.cleanup);\n23:   const manifest = await buildManifest(fixture.root);\n24:   const stale = await hydrateStyle(manifest, {\n25:     id: STYLE_ALPHA.id,\n26:     generationHash: 'sha256:stale',\n27:     mode: 'interface',\n28:   }, { corpusRoot: fixture.root });\n29:   assert.deepEqual(stale, { ok: false, error: 'generation-mismatch' });\n30: \n31:   const current = await hydrateStyle(manifest, {\n32:     id: STYLE_ALPHA.id,\n33:     generationHash: manifest.generationHash,\n34:     mode: 'interface',\n35:     includes: ['DESIGN.md'],\n36:     maxBytes: 128,\n37:   }, { corpusRoot: fixture.root });\n38:   assert.equal(current.ok, true);\n39:   assert.ok(current.totalBytes <= 128);\n40: \n41:   const bound = await bindHydrationManifest(manifest, {\n42:     id: STYLE_ALPHA.id,\n43:     generationHash: manifest.generationHash,\n44:     mode: 'interface',\n45:     includes: ['DESIGN.md'],\n46:   }, { corpusRoot: fixture.root });\n47:   assert.equal(bound.ok, true);\n48:   assert.equal(Object.isFrozen(bound.binding), true);\n49:   assert.equal(Object.isFrozen(bound.binding.request), true);\n50:   assert.equal(Object.isFrozen(bound.binding.liveManifest.styles[0].artifacts), true);\n51: });\n52: \n53: test('stale artifact hashes and unknown exact-reuse rights are refused', async (context) => {\n54:   const fixture = await createFixtureCorpus();\n55:   context.after(fixture.cleanup);\n56:   const manifest = await buildManifest(fixture.root);\n57:   const styleIndex = manifest.styles.findIndex((style) => style.id === STYLE_ALPHA.id);\n58:   const staleStyle = structuredClone(manifest.styles[styleIndex]);\n59:   const designIndex = staleStyle.artifacts.findIndex(\n60:     (artifact) => artifact.path.endsWith('/DESIGN.md'),\n61:   );\n62:   staleStyle.artifacts[designIndex].sha256 = artifactDigest('stale');\n63:   const craftedManifest = structuredClone(manifest);\n64:   craftedManifest.styles[styleIndex] = staleStyle;\n65:   const unavailable = await hydrateStyle(craftedManifest, {\n66:     id: STYLE_ALPHA.id,\n67:     generationHash: manifest.generationHash,\n68:     mode: 'interface',\n69:     includes: ['DESIGN.md'],\n70:   }, { corpusRoot: fixture.root });\n71:   assert.equal(unavailable.error, 'unavailable');\n72: \n73:   const rightsRestricted = await hydrateStyle(manifest, {\n74:     id: STYLE_ALPHA.id,\n75:     generationHash: manifest.generationHash,\n76:     mode: 'interface',\n77:     usage: 'exact-reuse',\n78:   }, { corpusRoot: fixture.root });\n79:   assert.equal(rightsRestricted.error, 'rights-restricted');\n80: });\n81: \n82: test('hydration rejects a same-generation record with another style source', async (context) => {\n83:   const fixture = await createFixtureCorpus();\n84:   context.after(fixture.cleanup);\n85:   const manifestPath = path.join(fixture.root, '_retrieval-manifest.json');\n86:   await runBuild(['--write'], { corpusRoot: fixture.root, manifestPath });\n87:   const poisoned = JSON.parse(await readFile(manifestPath, 'utf8'));\n88:   const alpha = poisoned.styles.find((style) => style.id === STYLE_ALPHA.id);\n89:   const beta = poisoned.styles.find((style) => style.id === STYLE_BETA.id);\n90:   const alphaSource = { slug: alpha.slug, artifacts: structuredClone(alpha.artifacts) };\n91:   alpha.slug = beta.slug;\n92:   alpha.artifacts = structuredClone(beta.artifacts);\n93:   beta.slug = alphaSource.slug;\n94:   beta.artifacts = alphaSource.artifacts;\n95:   await writeFile(manifestPath, `${JSON.stringify(poisoned, null, 2)}\\n`);\n96: \n97:   const result = await runHydrate({\n98:     id: STYLE_ALPHA.id,\n99:     generationHash: poisoned.generationHash,\n100:     mode: 'interface',\n101:     includes: ['DESIGN.md'],\n102:   }, { corpusRoot: fixture.root, manifestPath });\n103:   assert.deepEqual(result, { ok: false, error: 'manifest-stale' });\n104:   assert.deepEqual(Object.keys(result), ['ok', 'error']);\n105:   assert.equal(Object.isFrozen(result), true);\n106: });\n107: \n108: test('crafted traversal and escaping symlink paths return path-escape', async (context) => {\n109:   const fixture = await createFixtureCorpus();\n110:   context.after(fixture.cleanup);\n111:   const manifest = await buildManifest(fixture.root);\n112:   const ghostId = '44444444-4444-4444-8444-444444444444';\n113:   const ghostBase = {\n114:     ...manifest.styles[0],\n115:     id: ghostId,\n116:     slug: '_crafted',\n117:   };\n118: \n119:   const traversalManifest = {\n120:     ...manifest,\n121:     recordCount: manifest.recordCount + 1,\n122:     styles: [...manifest.styles, {\n123:       ...ghostBase,\n124:       artifacts: [{\n125:         path: '../outside/DESIGN.md',\n126:         bytes: 1,\n127:         sha256: artifactDigest('x'),\n128:       }],\n129:     }],\n130:   };\n131:   const traversal = await hydrateStyle(traversalManifest, {\n132:     id: ghostId,\n133:     generationHash: manifest.generationHash,\n134:     mode: 'interface',\n135:     includes: ['DESIGN.md'],\n136:   }, { corpusRoot: fixture.root });\n137:   assert.equal(traversal.error, 'path-escape');\n138: \n139:   const outsidePath = path.join(fixture.base, 'outside-design.md');\n140:   const content = 'outside';\n141:   await writeFile(outsidePath, content);\n142:   await mkdir(path.join(fixture.root, '_crafted'));\n143:   await symlink(outsidePath, path.join(fixture.root, '_crafted', 'DESIGN.md'));\n144:   const symlinkManifest = {\n145:     ...manifest,\n146:     recordCount: manifest.recordCount + 1,\n147:     styles: [...manifest.styles, {\n148:       ...ghostBase,\n149:       artifacts: [{\n150:         path: '_crafted/DESIGN.md',\n151:         bytes: Buffer.byteLength(content),\n152:         sha256: artifactDigest(content),\n153:       }],\n154:     }],\n155:   };\n156:   const symlinkEscape = await hydrateStyle(symlinkManifest, {\n157:     id: ghostId,\n158:     generationHash: manifest.generationHash,\n159:     mode: 'interface',\n160:     includes: ['DESIGN.md'],\n161:   }, { corpusRoot: fixture.root });\n162:   assert.equal(symlinkEscape.error, 'path-escape');\n163: });\n\n(End of file - total 163 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Hydration Generation and Path Guards                                    ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\nimport assert from 'node:assert/strict';\nimport { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\nimport { mkdir, readFile, symlink, writeFile } from 'node:fs/promises';\nimport path from 'node:path';\nimport test from 'node:test';\n\nimport { bindHydrationManifest, hydrateStyle } from '../hydrate.mjs';\nimport { buildManifest } from '../manifest.mjs';\nimport { runBuild, runHydrate } from '../style-library.mjs';\nimport { STYLE_ALPHA, STYLE_BETA, createFixtureCorpus } from './fixtures.mjs';\n\nfunction artifactDigest(content) {\n  return `sha256:${createHash('sha256').update(content).digest('hex')}`;\n}\n\ntest('hydration refuses a stale generation and honors byte caps', async (context) => {","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0093-sk-design-012-gap-research/.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/hydrate-guard.test.mjs","text":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Hydration Generation and Path Guards                                    ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\nimport assert from 'node:assert/strict';\nimport { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\nimport { mkdir, readFile, symlink, writeFile } from 'node:fs/promises';\nimport path from 'node:path';\nimport test from 'node:test';\n\nimport { bindHydrationManifest, hydrateStyle } from '../hydrate.mjs';\nimport { buildManifest } from '../manifest.mjs';\nimport { runBuild, runHydrate } from '../style-library.mjs';\nimport { STYLE_ALPHA, STYLE_BETA, createFixtureCorpus } from './fixtures.mjs';\n\nfunction artifactDigest(content) {\n  return `sha256:${createHash('sha256').update(content).digest('hex')}`;\n}\n\ntest('hydration refuses a stale generation and honors byte caps', async (context) => {\n  const fixture = await createFixtureCorpus();\n  context.after(fixture.cleanup);\n  const manifest = await buildManifest(fixture.root);\n  const stale = await hydrateStyle(manifest, {\n    id: STYLE_ALPHA.id,\n    generationHash: 'sha256:stale',\n    mode: 'interface',\n  }, { corpusRoot: fixture.root });\n  assert.deepEqual(stale, { ok: false, error: 'generation-mismatch' });\n\n  const current = await hydrateStyle(manifest, {\n    id: STYLE_ALPHA.id,\n    generationHash: manifest.generationHash,\n    mode: 'interface',\n    includes: ['DESIGN.md'],\n    maxBytes: 128,\n  }, { corpusRoot: fixture.root });\n  assert.equal(current.ok, true);\n  assert.ok(current.totalBytes <= 128);\n\n  const bound = await bindHydrationManifest(manifest, {\n    id: STYLE_ALPHA.id,\n    generationHash: manifest.generationHash,\n    mode: 'interface',\n    includes: ['DESIGN.md'],\n  }, { corpusRoot: fixture.root });\n  assert.equal(bound.ok, true);\n  assert.equal(Object.isFrozen(bound.binding), true);\n  assert.equal(Object.isFrozen(bound.binding.request), true);\n  assert.equal(Object.isFrozen(bound.binding.liveManifest.styles[0].artifacts), true);\n});\n\ntest('stale artifact hashes and unknown exact-reuse rights are refused', async (context) => {\n  const fixture = await createFixtureCorpus();\n  context.after(fixture.cleanup);\n  const manifest = await buildManifest(fixture.root);\n  const styleIndex = manifest.styles.findIndex((style) => style.id === STYLE_ALPHA.id);\n  const staleStyle = structuredClone(manifest.styles[styleIndex]);\n  const designIndex = staleStyle.artifacts.findIndex(\n    (artifact) => artifact.path.endsWith('/DESIGN.md'),\n  );\n  staleStyle.artifacts[designIndex].sha256 = artifactDigest('stale');\n  const craftedManifest = structuredClone(manifest);\n  craftedManifest.styles[styleIndex] = staleStyle;\n  const unavailable = await hydrateStyle(craftedManifest, {\n    id: STYLE_ALPHA.id,\n    generationHash: manifest.generationHash,\n    mode: 'interface',\n    includes: ['DESIGN.md'],\n  }, { corpusRoot: fixture.root });\n  assert.equal(unavailable.error, 'unavailable');\n\n  const rightsRestricted = await hydrateStyle(manifest, {\n    id: STYLE_ALPHA.id,\n    generationHash: manifest.generationHash,\n    mode: 'interface',\n    usage: 'exact-reuse',\n  }, { corpusRoot: fixture.root });\n  assert.equal(rightsRestricted.error, 'rights-restricted');\n});\n\ntest('hydration rejects a same-generation record with another style source', async (context) => {\n  const fixture = await createFixtureCorpus();\n  context.after(fixture.cleanup);\n  const manifestPath = path.join(fixture.root, '_retrieval-manifest.json');\n  await runBuild(['--write'], { corpusRoot: fixture.root, manifestPath });\n  const poisoned = JSON.parse(await readFile(manifestPath, 'utf8'));\n  const alpha = poisoned.styles.find((style) => style.id === STYLE_ALPHA.id);\n  const beta = poisoned.styles.find((style) => style.id === STYLE_BETA.id);\n  const alphaSource = { slug: alpha.slug, artifacts: structuredClone(alpha.artifacts) };\n  alpha.slug = beta.slug;\n  alpha.artifacts = structuredClone(beta.artifacts);\n  beta.slug = alphaSource.slug;\n  beta.artifacts = alphaSource.artifacts;\n  await writeFile(manifestPath, `${JSON.stringify(poisoned, null, 2)}\\n`);\n\n  const result = await runHydrate({\n    id: STYLE_ALPHA.id,\n    generationHash: poisoned.generationHash,\n    mode: 'interface',\n    includes: ['DESIGN.md'],\n  }, { corpusRoot: fixture.root, manifestPath });\n  assert.deepEqual(result, { ok: false, error: 'manifest-stale' });\n  assert.deepEqual(Object.keys(result), ['ok', 'error']);\n  assert.equal(Object.isFrozen(result), true);\n});\n\ntest('crafted traversal and escaping symlink paths return path-escape', async (context) => {\n  const fixture = await createFixtureCorpus();\n  context.after(fixture.cleanup);\n  const manifest = await buildManifest(fixture.root);\n  const ghostId = '44444444-4444-4444-8444-444444444444';\n  const ghostBase = {\n    ...manifest.styles[0],\n    id: ghostId,\n    slug: '_crafted',\n  };\n\n  const traversalManifest = {\n    ...manifest,\n    recordCount: manifest.recordCount + 1,\n    styles: [...manifest.styles, {\n      ...ghostBase,\n      artifacts: [{\n        path: '../outside/DESIGN.md',\n        bytes: 1,\n        sha256: artifactDigest('x'),\n      }],\n    }],\n  };\n  const traversal = await hydrateStyle(traversalManifest, {\n    id: ghostId,\n    generationHash: manifest.generationHash,\n    mode: 'interface',\n    includes: ['DESIGN.md'],\n  }, { corpusRoot: fixture.root });\n  assert.equal(traversal.error, 'path-escape');\n\n  const outsidePath = path.join(fixture.base, 'outside-design.md');\n  const content = 'outside';\n  await writeFile(outsidePath, content);\n  await mkdir(path.join(fixture.root, '_crafted'));\n  await symlink(outsidePath, path.join(fixture.root, '_crafted', 'DESIGN.md'));\n  const symlinkManifest = {\n    ...manifest,\n    recordCount: manifest.recordCount + 1,\n    styles: [...manifest.styles, {\n      ...ghostBase,\n      artifacts: [{\n        path: '_crafted/DESIGN.md',\n        bytes: Buffer.byteLength(content),\n        sha256: artifactDigest(content),\n      }],\n    }],\n  };\n  const symlinkEscape = await hydrateStyle(symlinkManifest, {\n    id: ghostId,\n    generationHash: manifest.generationHash,\n    mode: 'interface',\n    includes: ['DESIGN.md'],\n  }, { corpusRoot: fixture.root });\n  assert.equal(symlinkEscape.error, 'path-escape');\n});","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":163,"totalLines":163,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/__tests__/hydrate-guard.test.mjs","time":{"start":1784623544112,"end":1784623544146}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_079baf33226c216e016a5f31b7c95c8191aaa2af8df15f6503"}},"id":"prt_f83da36ec001kihKSYO02Eun5f","sessionID":"ses_07c31cbc4ffeYIOJJ8ZhDDe6Fl","messageID":"msg_f83d9c457001dsEnL1Wkw9V761"}}
